title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well in mixer or blender.
Add sugar and evaporated milk.
Beat well until blended.
Add vanilla.
Add milk.
Pour into 1-gallon freezer; freeze until firm 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cow pies
directions: In a double boiler, melt chips and shortening, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat; stir in raisins and almonds. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper. Chill until ready to serve. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat in 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown onion in butter until slightly brown; add meat.
Add flour and seasonings; blend well. Add water or part water and tomato juice.
Cover and cook slowly until tender, about 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.

title: green tomato jello jam
directions: Bring tomatoes and sugar to boil over low heat.
Boil 1/2 hour. Mash with eggbeater.
Mix to color thoroughly with small package of Jell-O (no water).
Strain and put into freezer containers. Freeze.

title: banana caramel spice pie
directions: Place banana slices in bottom of crust. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes and cinnamon. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours until set. Serve with caramel topping. Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach and chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken, adding salt to water, then dice.
Cook spinach; drain, but reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Saute onion in margarine; stir in spinach and chicken and set aside.
Combine soup, spinach broth, milk, chiles, sour cream and half the cheese; mix well. Stir half of sauce mixture into spinach and chicken mixture. Reserve remaining sauce.
Spoon chicken mixture evenly down center of each tortilla; roll up tortillas and place, seam side down, into 2 lightly greased 10 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Spoon remaining sauce on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.
This will make 8 large servings.

title: ham francisco
directions: Arrange ham and heat in shallow dish.
Heat through at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Drain peaches, saving syrup.
Saute green pepper and onions in margarine or butter about 4 minutes.
Add peach syrup to vegetables.
Mix the brown sugar, cornstarch and dry mustard together and add to vegetables.
Blend the catsup and lemon juice into the vegetables.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On a 12-inch round platter, layer ingredients in order.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and apples alternately.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: super-dooper cookies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar, brown sugar (packed), eggs and vanilla. Blend flour and baking soda; add and mix well.
Add chocolate chips, chopped nuts and raisins; blend.
Drop by ice cream scoop into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti with meat balls
directions: Mix the first ten ingredients and form into 1 1/2-inch balls. Pan-fry minced onion and the meat balls until browned in hot fat. Blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese, and simmer about 1 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add 2 eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, alternate with sour cream.
Add nut meats and vanilla.

title: sour milk chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Add to sugar and mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Alternate flour and sour milk (to which soda is added) and mix well.
Add beaten egg whites and vanilla; fold in until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake in 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon fluff coffee cake
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and spices together and add remaining ingredients.
Melt 1/3 cup of butter.
Pour over batter which has been placed in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zingy pesto for fish
directions: In a bowl, place chopped cilantro, white pepper, salt, fresh garlic, lemon and lime juice.
Add olive oil to ingredients.
Stir until all ingredients are combined.
Brush onto fish of your choice.
Place in refrigerator for an hour covered or until ready to grill or bake.
Grilling time 15 to 20 minutes depending on thickness of fish or bake in 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, as desired.

title: anne's mustard
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar and soak in a double boiler overnight. Cook until of desired consistency.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter and cinnamon in a pot and let melt.
Cut your biscuits up, then put them in butter until covered. Spread them in a Bundt pan and cook for 10 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: coke jello salad
directions: Bring 2 cups Coke
to
a boil.
Add jello and mix well. Add 2 cups
cold Coke.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts now or when mixture
begins
to
set.
Put in refrigerator until set. Makes 9 x
13-inch
pan
full.
You
can use small jello and 2 cups Coke for less.

title: yellow cake
directions: Note:
Use 1 fresh egg in place of the Egg Beaters and water.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Boil together
sugar,
water,
jello,
juice
and salt. Partially cool so it
doesn't
curdle;
add 2 1/2 cups milk or part cream if you
use orange jello; add 1/4 cup orange juice. Use any flavor jello you like.	Very good.

title: broccoli braised with white wine
directions: In heavy skillet, heat olive oil until a light haze forms over it.
Remove from heat and stir garlic in hot oil for 30 seconds. Return to moderate heat and toss broccoli flowerets in oil until they glisten.
Add wine, salt and a few grindings of pepper; simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer for another 15 minutes or until tender.
Quickly transfer with slotted spoon to heated bowl or deep platter.
Briskly boil liquid left in skillet over high heat until it has reduced to about 1/2 cup and pour it over broccoli.

title: big chicken bucket in the sky
directions: Mix flour, soup, Italian dressing and salt.
Put in bowl with cover.
Put 3 tablespoons in bread bag; shake on chicken.
Keep adding mixture as needed.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with butter, cut in squares.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: pansit (noodles)
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Saute with cooking oil the minced garlic, garlic powder and onion.
Add chicken, shrimp and half of the soy sauce.
Mix until cooked.
Add remaining vegetables; cook about 5 minutes.
Add water and noodles.
Mix well.
Serve warm. Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: banana fudge pie
directions: Cook pie crust according to package.
In a saucepan, melt 1/2 cup of little bits over low heat and remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup Cool Whip, eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool for 10 minutes.
Chill for 1 hour.
Layer bananas and remaining whipping topping. Top with little bits, if desired.

title: lemon delights
directions: Mix together the juices of the lemons and oranges and powdered sugar.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Put into small muffin tins. Bake for only a few minutes.
Dip while hot into juice mix.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chili baked pork spareribs
directions: Crack shinbones for easier serving.

In a small bowl, stir together chili powder, orange juice, oil, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, orange zest, honey, tomato paste, oregano, salt and pepper. With a sharp knife, slash a cross pattern into meaty side of ribs. Brush chili mixture over both sides of ribs, rubbing well into cross pattern.
Place ribs, meaty side down in a large foil-lined pan.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate for at least 24 to 48 hours.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash in very little water until tender.
Drain, mash and measure out 2 cups.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and render in skillet.
Remove rendered pieces with slotted spoon and discard.
Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips, 2 or 3-inches long.
Put 1/4 quantity of meat into skillet, browning quickly.
Repeat until all meat is cooked, then return meat to skillet.
Stir in soup mix and mushrooms with liquid; heat until bubbly and meat is tender.
Slowly stir in sour cream until blended, stirring constantly until heated.
Serve over noodles.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; remove from heat. Stir in sugar and coconut; shape into 3/4-inch balls. Chill until firm. Dip or drizzle chocolate over coconut balls. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: rice and chicken dish
directions: Mix together and put in pan.
Spread 6 to 8 chicken breasts on top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Great for those days at the pool. Dinner can cook while you swim!

title: spaghetti sauce - crock-pot
directions: Brown ground beef.
While ground beef is browning, cut up bell pepper and onion and cook with meat.
In a crock-pot, mix both cans of tomato sauce, can of tomato paste and browned meat with bell pepper and onion.
Cover with water and mix together.
Slow cook for 1 hour.
After 1 hour of cooking, stir in pack of spaghetti sauce seasoning.
Cook ingredients for an additional hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add 2 cups pecans.
Microwave 7 minutes on High; do not stir.
Remove bowl and place in cool water.
Add to pecan mixture the oleo and vanilla.
Stir well until mixture begins to turn a creamy color. Drop on buttered wax paper.
Makes 2/3 dozen small pralines.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary; arrange chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side up.
Broil until brown; stir sauce and pour over browned chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange lemon and pineapple around chicken.
Spoon sauce from baking pan over all; continue baking 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave for about 3 1/2 and 4 1/2 minutes. Pour in buttered 8 x 8 pan. Let set up and cut into squares.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk evenly over the crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake for 35 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: kielbasy - fresh
directions: Cut meat into 3/8-inch cubes.
Chop and crush garlic and mix with water.
Mix all spices, salt and garlic with the meat.
Pour 1 or 2 cups of tepid water over the mixture.
Let stand several hours before stuffing into the casing.

title: hash brown supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in a large, greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle with pepper, parsley and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Pound 6 tablespoons flour into sides of steak.
Brown in hot fat in skillet.
Add all of ingredients; cover.
Cook over low heat or in oven (275° to 300°) until tender (2 to 2 1/2 hours). Uncover last 15 minutes to cook down to thick sauce.

title: corn-cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Prepare pie filling according to package directions. Put cubes of cream cheese in medium saucepan, pour 1/3 of the prepared pie filling over the cubes and stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Let cool. Pour the plain lemon pie filling in the shell first (very important), then spread the lemon/cream cheese mixture evenly on top. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: macaroon torte
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Dissolve in hot water and chill until partially set.
Line side of an 8-inch square pan with macaroons. Roll remaining macaroons to cover bottom of pan, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Add pineapple to gelatin that has been added to whipped cream.
Pour into the pan. Top with remaining crumbs and chill thoroughly.
Serves 9.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box. Pour in drained tuna, onions, mixed vegetables, mushroom soup and milk. Cut up the margarine and fold in. Salt and pepper. Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: red coconut balls
directions: Mix red food coloring and sugar.
Mix vanilla, milk, Jell-O, coconut and pecans.
Chill for approximately 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in red sugar.
Makes 100 to 125.

title: angels delight
directions: Heat butter, sugar, eggs and dates in a pan, stirring constantly until it becomes a homogeneous mass.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Moisten hands.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pudding mix, undrained pineapple, marshmallows and pecans in large bowl until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping; cover.
Chill 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: blueberry pie - my favorite recipe
directions: Bake crust, flour, butter, 1/2 cup pecans, until brown.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and orange juice.
Stir in cranberries.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into cranberry mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup nuts.
Shape into ball and roll into crushed nuts.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in coffee and applesauce.
Mix in dry ingredients and add raisins and nuts. Chill 2 hours.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes. If desired, frost when cool with Lemon Butter Icing.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt shortening, blend in sugar.
Cool.
Stir in egg, then sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix. Cover casserole airtight with heavy aluminum foil.
Bake 2 hours without opening the foil at 350°.
Can be frozen after baking. Serves 6.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute shrimp and onion in butter for 10 minutes until tender, but not brown.
Add mushrooms and slowly saute a few more minutes.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in sour cream and cook gently for 10 minutes.
Add sherry and cook until well blended and hot.
Serve over rice.
Double recipe to feed 4 to 6 people.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add potato and pineapple.
Mix well and add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes) in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nuts if desired.
Frost.
Keeps well.

title: zesty broccoli rice bake
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook and drain the broccoli.
Combine the soups and Cheez Whiz in saucepan and heat until blended.
Combine onion mixture, soup mixture, cooked rice and broccoli.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with grated cheese and dash of paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: asparagus or artichoke pie
directions: Fry artichokes or asparagus with oil, onion and garlic until tender and onion is transparent.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt, pepper, parsley and baking powder.

title: oatmeal stuffing
directions: Mix together oleo and oatmeal.
Remove from stove and add onion and potato.
Soak toast in boiling water, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook hen until done; remove from bones and grind.
Mix with tomatoes and chili sauce into broth from hen.
Stir all together and cook for about 10 to 15 minutes; turn off heat and cool stew, then stir in the can of sweet milk and it is ready to eat.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add butter or margarine and other ingredients.
Pour in deep dish pie pan or 2 regular size pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and roll into bite size balls; fry.
Blend and heat in crock-pot Heinz chili sauce and grape jelly.
Add meatballs and simmer 2 hours or longer.

title: meatball stew
directions: In a bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 48 meatballs.
In a dutch oven; brown meatballs in oil; drain.
Add broth, soup potatoes, carrots and pearl onions; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: peppered ham
directions: Cook ham 15 minutes per pound.
Remove from oven; cut away rind.
Tear large strips of aluminum foil.
Mix brown sugar and black pepper on foil.
Pack on ham.
Wrap ham in foil; cook for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately pour off juices.

title: 4th of july jello
directions: Separately mix Jell-Os as directed.
Let stand.
In a glass trifle bowl, layer first the blue, cubed Jell-O, then Cool Whip and third, the sliced strawberries.
Place on Cool Whip.
Slice pound cake into little cubes.
Place in with strawberries.
Add blueberries.
Fourth, add more Cool Whip.
Fifth, add red Jell-O, cubed.
Top with a dab of Cool Whip and a strawberry to garnish.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and half cup of cream.
Then bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add remaining half cup of cream.
Cook slowly to very hard ball stage on oven at 260°. Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in 8-inch greased square pan.
Mark in squares when partially cool.
Cut when cold. Wrap caramels in wax paper and keep in a tight container.
Makes up to 100 pieces.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil. Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add. Beat until mixed well. Add carrots, pecans and flavoring. Grease and flour 4 pans. Divide batter evenly into pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash boiled potatoes; add remaining ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: boil cookies
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in pan on top of stove.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir this until it begins to thicken.
Spoon cookies out on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts.
Tear into bite-size pieces. Line 1 large or 2 small Pyrex dishes with crackers including sides. Layer all chicken on top of crackers.
Mix soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and sprinkle light layer on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine the dressings and mix well.
Mix together remaining ingredients, add dressing and mix lightly. Chill.

title: the wilky cookie
directions: Cream the first two ingredients well.
Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add flour, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Roll into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and press with a fork that has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese, eggs, onion and spinach.
Cook noodles for 10 minutes.
Layer 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, 3 noodles and 1/2 of cheese/spinach mixture.
Next, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with 3 noodles on top, sprinkled with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Set for 10 minutes, then slice.

title: tuna barley chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and flour in a 4-quart pan. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, about 1 hour or until barley is done.
Mix flour with milk.
Add to soup, stirring constantly, until thick.
Makes about 2 quarts of soup.

title: dietetic ice cream
directions: Make a cooked sauce with 1 cup of the milk and the flour.
Let cool, then add all other ingredients and stir well.
Freeze in either trays or freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and squeeze together.
Roll approximately 1 tablespoon of mixture into egg roll wrapper.
Beat an egg to seal corners.
Use as much oil as you'll need to deep fry egg rolls in wok.
Cook egg rolls approximately 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes about 25 rolls.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients on low speed for 4 minutes or until well blended. Scrape bowl often.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes back clean.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: crab strata
directions: Dice 4	slices	of bread and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan
or dish.
Mix crab, mayonnaise, onion, celery and soup. Spread
over the diced bread.
Dice remaining bread and place over crab mixture.
Beat eggs and milk.	Pour over bread and
crab mixture.
Sprinkle	grated cheese on top.
Place in refrigerator for
several
hours or even better if left overnight.
Bake
for
1 hour or until puffed and brown. Makes 8 or 10 large servings.

title: huge pot of clam chowder
directions: You will need 1 large, stainless steel pot.

title: herb bubble ring
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease tube pan.
Mix cheese, parsley, basil, garlic powder and paprika; reserve.
Mix baking mix, sour cream and milk until soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Knead dough 10 times.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip each ball into melted margarine.
Roll in cheese mix. Arrange balls 1/4-inch apart in layers in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese mixture over top.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen edges from side.
Remove from pan.

title: cauliflower-leek puree(low carb mashed potato alternative)
directions: Cook Cauliflower and leek in salted water until very soft (approx 15 min.).
Drain.
Return veggies to pot to heat and dry. Place 1/2 of veggies plus 1/2 of remaining ingredients in food processor.
Process until smooth.
Repeat with rest of mixture.

title: pasta with stir-fried sesame beef
directions: Halve the flank steak lengthwise with the grain.
Cut each piece across the grain into 1/4-inch wide slices.
In a medium bowl, combine 1 tablespoon of the sesame oil, 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce and the black pepper.
Stir to combine.
Add the steak slices; toss to coat evenly.
Cover loosely; set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits in mixture; arrange in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts. Melt oleo and stir in brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Let loaf of bread thaw in fridge overnight (wrap in wax paper). Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
After it is thawed, grease a Bundt pan.
Pinch off small pieces of bread dough and roll into balls.
Dip balls into melted butter, then roll balls in mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Layer bread balls in Bundt pan.
Cover pan with wet dish cloth.
Let dough rise in warm place until dough reaches top of pan, 4 to 5 hours.

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans, spices and veggies in broth for 1 hour. Add chicken and cook for 15 minutes. Serve with sour cream and Monterey Jack cheese.

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon; set aside. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Beat in bananas and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture and oats until mixed well.
Stir in nuts.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add applesauce and 1/2 cup water.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add in shortening mixture and beat with electric mixer.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rotini salad
directions: Put in jar; let stand overnight.

title: corn bake
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add corn, muffin mix and onion.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together sugar and corn oil.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: delicious bean soup
directions: Boil the beans in the water for 2 minutes before removing them from the heat to let stand for 1 hour.
Then add the ham bone, garlic and bay leaf to the beans.
Cover and simmer them for 2 hours or until the ingredients are almost tender.
Add the vegetables and salt and pepper to taste; simmer them for 1 hour longer.
Remove the ham bone; cut off the meat and dice it to add to the beans.
Reheat the soup almost to boiling; then remove the bay leaf.

title: broccoli grape salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, grapes, celery, onion, water chestnuts, raisins and almonds. Mix yogurt, mayonnaise and honey. Pour dressing over broccoli mixture and gently stir. Cover and refrigerate before serving. Yields 4 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Form walnut size balls and bake
on ungreased cookie sheet for 5 to 6 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool for awhile before moving from cookie sheet.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add flavoring, shortening and 2/3 cup of the milk.
Beat 2 minutes and add remaining 1/3 cup milk and 2 unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 minutes more. Pour into 2 round 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken with carbonara sauce
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine margarine and oil and heat until margarine is melted; add chicken and cook over medium high heat, turning once, until cooked through and lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer to plate and set aside.

title: country ham
directions: Boiling Method:
Soak
ham
overnight.	Wash thoroughly in warm water.
Use a stiff brush
to remove any surface mold. Place ham in boiler, skin side down.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 25 minutes
per
pound.
(Keep covered with water while simmering.) When done,
remove
skin	while
still warm.

title: bean soup
directions: Put hamburger, onion and bell pepper in skillet; cook until meat is done.
Simmer a bit.
Add beans and tomatoes; let simmer awhile.
Good over rice.

title: chinese mushroom chow yoke
directions: Brown thinly sliced meat and onions in oil, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and water.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine cornstarch, salt, pepper, brown sauce, soy sauce, cold water and brown sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Stir into first mixture.
Stir constantly to avoid burning, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Line 24 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with liners.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and peanut butter until coarse crumbs.
Follow package directions, omitting oil.
Spoon some batter to half full in cups.
Top each with 1 teaspoon jelly.
Cover each with more batter to fill.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove and frost.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mother's oats spice cookies
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Mix all dry ingredients, adding rolled oats last.
Melt shortening and mix with brown sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Pour in milk, then add dry ingredients and raisins.
Drop on greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
This was our grandmother Folks' recipe.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Form into 1-inch meatballs (with the exception of cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice) and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Heat cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice until dissolved.
Then pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover first 30 minutes while baking so they don't get too brown.

title: apple crisp for one
directions: Place apple slices in a small bowl.
Combine oats, walnuts, sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apple.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes until tender.
Let stand 1 minute.
Makes 1 serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil together and then set aside.
Mix flour, soda, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon together.
To this mixture, add the Karo, buttermilk, vanilla, nuts and prunes.
(Cook prunes 20 minutes; drain and let cool.) Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Ice with Caramel Icing (if desired).

title: polpette(italian meatballs)
directions: Mix all ingredients (raisins may be added to mixture for flavor).
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or meatballs can also be fried in pan with oil to cover bottom of pan.
Cook until done.
Add to tomato sauce whether baked or fried.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until half done. Brown ground beef and onions. Drain. Layer potatoes and ground beef in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix Cheddar cheese soup and 1/2 cup milk. Pour over beef and potatoes. Pour tomato sauce over mixture. Sprinkle on pepper, oregano and Parmesan cheese. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 375° oven, covered with foil. Uncover. Put on Mozzarella cheese and melt.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 325° no longer than 40 to 45 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: Add water to concentrates as per directions.
Add nectar and lemon juice in punch bowl.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet. Pour Vernors down side of bowl and serve.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add vanilla. Gradually stir potato chips and flour. Drop rounded teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes. Cool on paper and sprinkle with powered sugar.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Cook pepper, onion, carrots and garlic for about 5 minutes in saucepan with oil or bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, mashed into small pieces.
Stir in beans with salt, pepper, etc., simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
It freezes, too!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and apples.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Next morning, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add to cranberry mixture.
When chilled, but not set, add celery and nuts.
Refrigerate to set.

title: deviled cheese sandwich
directions: Combine cheese, onion and pimientos or pepper.
Add eggs, seasoning and mayonnaise; mix well.
Spread on bread or crackers. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: crab and spinach dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add crab meat, spinach and cheese to taste.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetables.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease pan.
Spread out dough to form crust.
Put on sausage, hash browns and eggs.
Put on optional items if desired.
Put cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Bake at 375°.

title: nut candy
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture reaches 230° or just before the soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add vanilla flavoring and 2 1/2 cups of nuts.
Stir until mixture starts to lose its shine and hardens slightly.
Quickly turn out on wax paper.
Separate into individual pieces.
Cool.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crumble the graham crackers with a rolling pin, mix with melted butter and press in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make Jell-O according to package directions, but use only half the water.
Refrigerate until set.
In blender, mix together cream cheese, condensed milk, the Jell-O and the lemon juice.
Pour into cake pan over graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: house dressing
directions: To the bottle of dressing, add remaining ingredients and shake well. Refrigerate 24 hours to blend flavors.

title: meringue surprises *
directions: Beat together the egg whites, vanilla and salt.
(I add a small amount of cream of tartar also.)
Beat until stiff but not dry. Gradually beat in sugar until stiff and satiny.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Line cookie tray with brown paper. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Strain broth that chicken was cooked in and place back in pot. Cook noodles in broth until done. Take 2 1/2 cups of broth out and add soups and sour cream. Drain noodles, then add soup mixture and chicken. Combine margarine and stuffing, then sprinkle over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate meringue puffs
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over warm water.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until soft peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in chocolate and nuts. Drop on greased sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on the box, using the cold milk.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip until well blended. Layer a casserole dish with vanilla wafers, then bananas.
Spread a layer of the pudding over banana layer.
Continue alternating layers.
End with wafers.
Refrigerate 1 to 3 hours before serving.

title: lazy lady pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with vinegar and spices. Let set for 6 weeks in a cool, dark place. Stir once a week. At the end of 6 weeks, drain off vinegar, add sugar and let set for 24 hours.

title: lime vodka slush
directions: Mix and freeze. Serve with 7-Up, Sprite or Slice.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for about 1 hour, or until chicken is tender.
Serve over spaghetti.
Top with your favorite cheese.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute 8 minutes.
Add next 6 ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Toss with bread cubes.
Beat egg with chicken broth and mix into bread cubes.
Shape into 2-inch balls and place on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375 oven for 20 minutes.
Makes about 26 to 30 balls.
Freeze well also.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder. Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake in a slow oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Cut while hot and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked apples
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Pour orange juice in pan.
Put apples in and cover with remaining ingredients (mix all together and pour over apples).
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and lima beans until slightly cooked. Brown and drain hamburger and add to vegetables. Add corn, juice, onion and sauce. Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for about 2 hours.

title: spiral pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until soft; drain. Cut up all veggies. Mix together. Add dressing. Sprinkle with seasonings for flavor. Chill 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugar with eggs, oil, sour cream and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend flour, sugar, eggs, melted margarine and vanilla. Stir in chocolate bits, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35
minutes, until firm, in a preheated 350° oven.

title: baked chicken and broccoli
directions: In oblong 9 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange cut up or whole or half, cleaned chicken breast.
Sprinkle rice over top and salt and pepper.
Put can of soup on top of that.
Add fresh cut up broccoli and 1 cup water.
Add Cheddar cheese (optional) and cover dish. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Good and tender.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, alternately, with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until done.

title: refrigerator peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and
chips
in
a
big double boiler (don't boil). Fold in
nuts and cornflakes.
Stir gently until coated. Drop by spoonfuls
onto waxed paper on cookie sheets. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Work butter into dry ingredients (only 2 tablespoons sugar) until mealy.
Put mixture on the bottom and up sides of an 8-inch square pan.
Press firmly.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over oatmeal, molasses, salt and shortening.
When lukewarm, dissolve yeast in mixture.
Mix in enough flour to make a bread dough.
Knead and put into a bowl to rise.
Shape into 4 loaves. Let rise again and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in serving size pieces.
Place in an oblong baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Mix soup and milk and pour over top.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add peanuts and cinnamon.
Boil over medium heat one half hour or until there is no syrup left.
Watch carefully and stir.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: dusty's beans and rice
directions: Cook pepper and onion in skillet in small amount of oil until soft.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook together for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Whip.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Whip again.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into two 8 x 9-inch graham cracker pie crusts.
Freeze.
When solid top with additional topping and freeze again.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut.

title: strawberry party salad
directions: Add water, juice and jello to marshmallows.
Chill until slightly firm.
Add pineapple and strawberries.

title: white trash
directions: Mix raisins, peanuts and Rice Chex together.
Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over raisins, peanuts and Rice Chex; mix together.
Pour box of confectioners sugar over mixture; mix until well coated.

title: peach pie
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl and blend together, then add chopped peaches.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Makes 2 pies.
Store in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix the flour, pecans and melted margarine together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar, lemon juice and Cool Whip together.
Spread over cooked and cooled crust, then add the cherry pie filling.

title: orange coconut chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter in large bowl; slowly add sugar.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine orange juice and water; blend with butter mixture.
Blend in flour and cornmeal.
Fold in coconut.
Divide mixture into 2 pie crusts. Bake until golden, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: "party" chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Turn into shallow, buttered casserole.
Mix cheese and potatoes chips and sprinkle over the top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 16 to 20.

title: deluxe cornbread
directions: Mix, pour into greased pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Add tomato soup, mushroom soup, tomato paste and Cheez Whiz until mixed well. Boil macaroni, then rinse.
Layer meat sauce and macaroni until casserole dish is filled.
Bake on 350° for 35 minutes.
This dish is best served with salad and yeast rolls.
Serves 6 to 8 adults.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the above ingredients. Mix with wooden spoon.
Add nuts and mix.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and one egg.
Press this into bottom of ungreased cake pan.
Beat cream cheese and 2 eggs together; add confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy chili dip
directions: In medium bowl, with
mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
With mixer at low speed, gradually add V-8 juice until thoroughly blended.
Stir in chilies, onions, olives, red pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and refrigerate at least four hours before serving.
Garnish with fresh parsley. Serve with bagel chips or vegetables.

title: chocolate chip cookies 1
directions: Mix and spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, milk, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Dilute soup with the milk.
Arrange artichokes in casserole. Add layer of eggs, olives and water chestnuts.
Cover with soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: taffy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove 1/2 cup of dough and reserve for another use.
Roll dough into 14-inch circle on a 15-inch baking stone or pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, or until slightly browned. Let cool 10 minutes, then loosen from stone or pan.
Cool completely.
Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, brown sugar, and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cookie.
Peel, core and slice apples very thinly and dip into soda pop, then arrange on cookie. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat caramel and drizzle over apples. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut and serve.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cherry icebox delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into cake pan.
Set in icebox at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate delicacies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a cookie sheet with tinfoil and arrange crackers so they completely cover the foil.
Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 3 minutes.
Immediately after removing from oven, pour chips over.
Spread chocolate when melted.
Cool, then refrigerate until set.
Flip over and peel back tinfoil.
Cut and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended and batter is smooth. Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven and glaze while cake is still hot.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour
and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, coconut extract and coconut.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs in melted butter and sprinkle with paprika. Cook until it bubbles.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake yellow cake in sheet cake pan as directed on box.
While cake is baking, mix small can of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand condensed milk.
When cake is done (while it is still warm), punch holes all in cake with a fork and the pour the mixture over cake. Put cake in refrigerator and cool.
Then top with medium container of Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt, carrots, raisins, pecans and apple.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overblend.

title: apple breakfast cake
directions: Hand knead the butter into the flour, baking powder and sugar.
Gently beat the egg, vanilla and milk.
Add into the flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.

Grease 12x18 pan, pour in 3/4 of the batter, sprinkle with cinnamon and cloves, spread the pie mixture over it, then cover with remaining batter.	Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel pie
directions: Mix flour and butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pat down evenly.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown; cool.
Spread caramel ice cream topping on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour on top of ice cream topping.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill several hours before serving.

title: layered meat loaf
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery together in butter with garlic until onions are clear.
Set aside to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.
Mix together the salad dressing, sugar and vinegar; toss with the salad. Serves 4.

title: pineapple candy
directions: Place pineapple, sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, marshmallows, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan; cut into squares.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Wash and drain vegetables. Build salad in layers in glass bowl. Begin with lettuce, green onions, celery and peas. Dot pea layer with pimientos and add water chestnuts on top. In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sweetener and garlic powder until creamy. Spread dressing over salad and garnish with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Grease casserole.
Wash and slice zucchini.
Alternate layers of zucchini, cracker crumbs, grated cheese, butter, tomatoes, brown sugar and sliced onions.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(After first 30 minutes, uncover and check.)

title: antioquian beans
directions: Wash the beans and let soak overnight.
Put beans and bacon or salt pork in a pressure cooker with enough water to cover.
Cook for about an hour or until tender.
Add the plantains and cook until they are soft.
Add the salt and mix well.
Apart, saut the tomatoes, onions and garlic until soft; then add to the beans. Cook another half an hour, until all flavors are absorbed.
These beans are even better the day after.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Have pie crust ready.
Makes a 9-inch pie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then lower heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: come back sandwiches
directions: Make cream sauce with oleo, flour and milk.
Add eggs.
Cook until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, pimento, nuts and green olives.
Spread on bread.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended. Add the eggs and mix well.
Pour batter into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
Let chill for 3 hours.

title: different celery sticks
directions: Clean celery well.
Cut each stick into 2 1/2-inch pieces. Mix together cream cheese, pineapple, nuts, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Fill celery pieces with mixture and arrange on platter.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix sugar, shortening, water, salt and eggs together.
Add yeast and flour to mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough into pie-shaped circles, about 3 hours before serving.
Spread with melted butter.
Cut into 16 triangles. Roll from large end to small end; let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mostaccioli-broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook mostaccioli to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with hot water.

title: microwave quiche
directions: Remove pastry from foil to glass pie dish.
Microwave at High 1/2 to 1 minute until softened.
With fingers, press firmly in pie plate.
Brush inside with Worcestershire sauce.
Prick pastry. Place pie plate in the oven on trivet or inverted saucer. Microwave at High, 3 to 4 minutes, rotating plate 1/2 turn after minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over bottom of pie shell.
With fork, beat together eggs, cream and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over cheese in pie shell.
Microwave at Medium-high, 11 to 13 minutes, rotating pie 1/2 turn after 6 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes to firm slightly before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine the syrup, butter and peppermint extract; beat until well blended.
Gradually add 2 cups of the powdered sugar, beating well.
Stir in as much of the remaining powdered sugar as you can with a spoon.
Turn out onto a surface lightly coated with a little powdered sugar.
Knead in enough of the remaining powdered sugar to make a stiff dough that is smooth.
Divide into thirds.
Using 1/3 of the dough, knead the red food coloring in until evenly distributed.
Knead the green food coloring into another 1/3 of the dough.
Leave the remaining dough white.
Shape the dough into 3/4 inch balls; place 2 inches apart on baking sheets lined with wax paper.
Press with tines of a fork.
In necessary, dip the fork in powdered sugar to prevent sticking.
Let dry several hours.
Makes about 75 mints.

title: honey mustard coleslaw
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, honey and mustard in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine salmon, mayonnaise, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, spread on buttered toasted bread or crackers.
Sprinkle with red pepper; garnish with watercress sprigs.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Combine
and
bake in pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Tastes like pork!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix onion, meal and flour together, then add well beaten egg and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.
When done, they will float to top.
Makes about 16 hush puppies.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices off cherries, pineapple and oranges.
Use these juices to make pudding.
After pudding cools, put it over fruits.

title: cheesy green bean and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine water, butter and stuffing mix. Set aside.

Season chicken with cajun seasoning or salt and pepper. In preheated, buttered large skillet cook chicken over medium-high heat until center is no longer pink and outside is deep brown. Cube into 1-inch pieces.
In same skillet, combine soup, milk, green beans and chicken over heat.
Place mixture in a 2-quart baking dish.
Spread stuffing evenly over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot veggies
directions: Pre-cook California mix until tender; drain.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and 1/2 of onions to vegetables.
Grease dish.
Mix soup and cheese with vegetables; put in casserole dish.
Put rest of onions on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, white syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and stir down. Pour over popped corn.
Stir corn to cover all.
Put corn on cookie sheet.
Put in oven and bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: the kids favorite stroganoff
directions: Saute meat with onion, celery and mushrooms.
Season with Mrs. Dash, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Add beef bouillon.
Simmer until seasonings are blended.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch.
Add sour cream.
Cook just until heated through.
Serve over rice or pasta.
(A "lighter" version can be made by substituting ground turkey and nonfat sour cream.)
Delish with green beans and fresh green salad.

title: diabetic french apple pie
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Place in pie crust and bake 50 minutes at 425°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash with fork and add enough of the liquid from the shrimp to desired consistency.

title: hamburger-bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Stir until brown and crumbly.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except potato chips. Pour into casserole dish. Top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Heat turmeric, salt, mustard seed, vinegar and sugar to boiling.
Pour over cabbage, green pepper and onion.
This will keep in refrigerator 2 or 3 weeks.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat. Place tea bags in water and cover.
Steep for 6 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add spices.
Cover and set aside for 30 minutes.
Remove spices and add apple juice, lemon juice, orange juice, cranberry juice and Jello.
Let set for at least a day to achieve best flavor.
Serve hot.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Spread mixture of first 6 ingredients on platter, then top with 3/4 cup chili sauce.
Top with crab meat, fresh or frozen.

title: liverwurst igloo
directions: In a food processor, combine liver sausage, 1/2 cream cheese, dill pickles, dill juice, onion, hot sauce and garlic.
Process until well blended.
Line a 2 to 3 cups bowl with plastic wrap; pack mixture inside.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix reserved cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Invert chilled liver mixture onto a serving plate.
Peel off plastic.
Spread cheese mixture over liver to cover.
Sprinkle parsley over top. Serve chilled.

title: triple chocolate pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes 30 minutes until tender. Drain and mash. Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Add potatoes and the rest of ingredients. Put in 2 quart casserole dish greased. Refrigerate overnight. Take out 15 minutes before baking; uncover and put paprika over top. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend all except chipped beef; add it by hand.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel apples and take core out.
Sprinkle each apple thoroughly with brown sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Fill each apple (middle) with a mixture of the relish, raisins, nuts and orange rind.
Bake in a nonstick pan with cranberry juice filling the bottom of the pan. Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours or until you see they are soft.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent roll dough.
Press dough on large baking sheet; seal edges.
Bake for 7 minutes. Cool.
Combine salad dressing, cream cheese and dry Ranch dressing mix and dill; mix well.
Spread evenly over crust.
Cut vegetables up in small slices or pieces.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese.
Pat down lightly.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: christmas pea salad
directions: Combine broccoli flowerets, cauliflower flowerets, chopped green onions, chopped green pepper and any other crunchy vegetable you wish.
Over vegetables, pour 1 bottle Italian dressing and mix.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: yogurt-herb dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Keep in covered dish in refrigerator.
It will keep several days.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; save juice (3 cups fruit juice).
Cook puddings with
juice until thick.
Cool.
Add fruits and chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
May add any fresh fruit or nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place casserole in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° until a silver knife inserted off center comes out clean.

title: 7-up biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, sour cream and 7-Up.
Put on floured board or cloth and roll and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet sprayed with butter flavored Pam.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all together and just before serving, add mayonnaise, just enough to blend the ingredients to preferred consistency.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and mix with egg mixture. Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into well-greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when still warm.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Add buttermilk or sour milk for desired batter.
More milk for thinner cakes, less for fat cakes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water and salt.
Turn burner on high until it starts to boil, then boil 10 minutes.
Turn off burner and let stand 10 minutes.
Before removing, cover, then add milk.
Simmer on low heat until it starts to thicken, stirring often, then add egg, vanilla and sugar.
Dot with butter and top with cinnamon.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bouillon, in large bowl.
Roll out into a rectangle.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with salt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Then add pineapple, sliced bananas, nuts and cherries.
Whip whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into pan and freeze firmly. When frozen, slice and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 10.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Place powdered milk, sugar, shortening and salt in extra large bowl.
Add 5 cups warm water.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix. Add dissolved yeast mixture.
Keep adding flour until dough is formed.
Use hands and mix well. Make a soft dough.
Let rise. Punch down.
Repeat 2 more times.
Melt margarine in pan.
Roll dough into small bread size stick shapes.
Place 12 to 13 of these rolls in each bread pan.
Pour some melted margarine all over each loaf.
Let rise.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: crescent roll puffs
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Dip marshmallow in melted butter, then roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wrap a crescent roll around the marshmallow, sealing all edges.
Dip the roll in melted butter and roll in cinnamon-sugar.
Place roll in muffin pan.
Do the same for other marshmallows.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or whatever directions on roll package.
Cool slightly, then remove from pan.
Drizzle with icing if you like.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Combine flour and salt; sift twice. Cream butter and add sugar gradually. Add milk and vanilla. Stir into flour, blending in dates and nuts. Roll into 1-inch balls and place about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fresh orange pecan muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, whip margarine and sugar until light. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Put orange pieces, raisins and pecans into a food processor.
Process on high for about 20 seconds, until it forms a thick mixture.
Fold this mixture into the muffin batter.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Chop bell pepper and onion.
Place in large bowl.
Mix 1 cup sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat, add 2/3 cup oil.
Pour over cabbage while still hot.
Cool to serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add soda to flour.
Add alternately flour and sour cream to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in a large greased and floured tube pan at 300 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.
Cake should have a nice brown crust on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: food processor secrets
directions: In food processor, combine flour, butter, pecans, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, vanilla and almond.
Process well.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into balls, using 1 tablespoon each.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until set but not brown. Let stand 1 minute.
Place hot cookies in the 2 cups sugar; roll to coat each cookie.
Cool completely; roll again.
Keep in airtight container.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: *Can also use 3 pounds cooked ground beef.

title: pecan cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 cup pecans. Press in spring-form pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine cooked rice with milk, butter, salt, sugar, eggs, vanilla and raisins. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Place on rack or metal trivet in slow cooking pot.
Add 1 cup water to pot.
Cover and cook on high for 2 hours.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute; beat well.
Stir in flavorings. Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, beating well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press an almond slice onto the center of each cookie. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Remove cookies to wire racks and cool completely.

title: ida's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Add the oil, eggs, pumpkin, and water.
Mix well.
Pour into greased small loaf pans or cans.
Fill half full.

title: granny's bourbon slush
directions: Steep tea in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and freeze. Serve and enjoy.

title: old fashion potato bread
directions: Make potatoes for 2 servings as label directs, omitting margarine.
Measure 1 cup.
In a large bowl put in water and sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Use electric mixer.
Mix at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add 4 cups of flour and mix with hands until smooth and stiff enough to leave bowl.
Turn out onto floured tabletop.
Use 1/4 cup flour if more is needed.

title: toss and bake potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Toss potatoes with dressing and cheese, mixed.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, until lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange slaw(heart healthy)
directions: Combine dressing and orange juice; blend well. Add coleslaw and oranges. Toss gently. Makes 4 3/4 servings. 100 calories, 4 grams fat.

title: fried peach pie
directions: Boil peaches until tender.
Drain, mash with fork and sweeten to taste.
Put on half of a pie shell, put other half of pie shell down over peaches.
Use prongs of wet fork to seal crust.
Fry in oil, turn over and fry other side until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except broccoli, oleo, and stuffing). Line oblong 9 x 13-inch baking dish with broccoli.
Spoon mixture over broccoli.
Melt oleo.
Mix with stuffing.
Cover top of casserole with the mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Chop beef.
Mix all ingredients over medium heat.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix cheeses, mayonnaise, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce together well.
Form log and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: berried chocolate cake
directions: Cake:
Whisk together flour, cocoa and salt.
In top of double boiler, combine eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir over gently simmering water until mixture is slightly warmed.
Turn into large mixer bowl and beat until thick in volume.
Fold in flour and butter mixture, a third at a time.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven; cool for 10 minutes.
Loosen and turn onto rack.
Cool for 2 hours at room temperature.

title: old-fashioned banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Place all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Mix with an electric mixer until thoroughly combined.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Test with straw for doneness.)
One cup chopped nuts makes it even better.

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, add meat, soups and 1 cup soda. Stir, then cover.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Cook noodles, add butter, salt and pepper.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by large spoon or roll in balls and flatten for monsters.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: caramel dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Serve with sliced apples (dip apples in lemon juice to keep from turning brown).

title: helen's carrot casserole
directions: Saute one at a time carrots, green pepper and onion until tender.
Alternate layers of vegetables and soup in 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and heated thoroughly.

title: eastern shore crab cakes
directions: Mix lightly into the meat without breaking down the lumps. Make into cakes and let set for a couple of hours under refrigeration.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into large container.
Freeze.
Cut and serve.

title: salsa
directions: Saute onions, garlic and chilies in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add tomato sauce or crushed tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 15 minutes on low.

title: bev's mother's heath bars
directions: Break crackers into quarters.
Line cookie sheet with crackers.
Set aside.
In saucepan melt butter with sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bring to boil and allow to boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and transfer each piece to wax paper.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slices from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside. Heat 1 c. water and 1/2 tsp. salt to boiling.
Add peppers and cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/3 of the meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased 8x8x2 inch baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.
Makes 2-3 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots and combine with remaining ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls; freeze.
Allow 1 hour to defrost before baking.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 30.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; save 2 tablespoons of fat.
Drain sausage on paper towel.
Saute onions, bell peppers and mushrooms in fat saved.
Mix flour and cheese.
Add sausage, onions, mushrooms and bell peppers.
Add spices.
Pour into pie crust.
Mix evaporated milk and eggs.
Pour over pie.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven or until done.

title: no peekie stew
directions: Cooking Time: 3 hours.
Servings: 4 to 6.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: pecan pie (2)
directions: Beat eggs, add syrup, pecans, sugar, butter, and flour. Combine mixture well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks and granulated sugar until thoroughly mixed. Add milk and heavy cream; beat thoroughly.
Add brandy and rum; beat thoroughly.

title: georgia peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together in a bowl.
In another bowl with a wooden spoon, beat shortening and sugar; add peanut butter and blend well. Add raisins; cover and chill for an hour.
Drop on baking sheet, 2 inches apart, and bake until brown (10 to 12 minutes).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except dried onions.
Sprinkle dried onions over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil
in
iron skillet. Add rice, onion and celery. Heat quickly
until
rice
turns opaque.
Stir in tomatoes and juice. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Turn off heat and leave covered 5 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: baked egg and sausage(good for brunch)
directions: Press crescent rolls in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Be sure to press perforations together.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, pepper and green pepper.
Place crumbled sausage on roll crust.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage mix and add egg mixture and bake at 350° until well done in middle.
Test with knife.
It is done when knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate bits cake
directions: Combine chopped dates, boiling water and baking soda.
Cool. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add date mixture and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Put into an 8 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate bits, nuts and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Stir in buttermilk, butter and egg just until combined. Fold in apples and almonds.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Cool. Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Salt and pepper the ribs.
Brown in bacon drippings in large Dutch oven.
Pour mixture of all other ingredients over ribs. Cover and cook in 300° oven until well done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: snow drift pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cut in Snow Drift until texture of meal. Add all ingredients and beat at high speed for 6 to 8 minutes. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix oleo, flour, pecans and sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together until creamy.
Add whipped topping, folding in until well mixed.
Spread this mixture over cooled crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Combine and cook first 4 ingredients until tender; set aside.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Cook and mash potatoes as usual.
Salt (but don't use butter). Add cream cheese and beaten egg.
Add green onion and parsley. Beat well; transfer to well-greased 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes; cool.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and tea; chill.
When ready to serve, pour into punch bowl containing ice.
Add ginger ale and float vanilla ice cream. Stir frequently until frothy.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut cake filling
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Fold in coconut, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Dip with a cup and spread on cooled layers of yellow cake.
This is best when allowed to sit for 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: clam chowder
directions: Sauteed in 3-quart pot margarine, onions and sweet pepper on medium to high heat until onions are clear.
Add clams with juice, black pepper, salt, lemon juice, Texas Pete and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Simmer at medium heat for 10 minutes.
Turn to low heat; add milk while stirring.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes (do not allow to boil).
In 3 ounce cup add cornstarch and 3 ounces milk; stir until lumps are gone, then pour mixture into chowder, stirring well.
Cook 10 more minutes while still stirring.
Take off heat and let sit while covered for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Put flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt into small bowl.
Add egg whites and beat on #10 speed until stiff (about 1/2
minute).
Beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat only until soft peaks are formed.
Add milk, flavoring and shortening; beat on #2 speed.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Pour gelatin on top of cold water to soften.
Put tomato soup in pan, add cream cheese.
Heat on low to melt cheese.
Add gelatin and the rest of the ingredients.
Stir and pour into Jello mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: spinach and spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine egg, yogurt, milk, half the grated Parmesan, onion, salt and pepper.
Add Monterey Jack cheese.
Mix well.
Add the spinach and spaghetti; turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining grated Parmesan.
Bake, covered, for about 15 minutes
at 350°. Uncover and bake for about 15 minutes more, until bubbling and slightly browned.
A cup of chopped or diced ham is a nice addition.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Continue baking, uncovered, until done, about 1 hour.

title: cabernet cranberry sauce
directions: Bring sugar and red wine to boil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add cranberries, orange rind, and cinnamon stick.
Return to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, and simmer, partially covered, about 15-20 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Remove and discard cinnamon stick.
Cool slightly; serve warm, or chill for 2 hours, if desired.

title: red kidney bean sauce
directions: In skillet, combine olive oil, salt, oregano and onion.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Kidney beans should be rinsed well to get rid of juice.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer for additional 10 minutes.
Serve hot over bed of rice.

title: quick lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly until well mixed. Pour at once into graham cracker crust. Chill 1 hour before serving. Serves 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine wine and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken mixture. Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Reserve marinade.
Combine mayonnaise and reserved marinade.
Put salad on lettuce and serve with mayonnaise mixture.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding(light recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients; add bread and stir well.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish that has been coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place dish in a larger shallow pan; add water to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg together.
Then add eggs, oil, prunes and nuts.
Cook in microwave on Medium for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix flour and sugar together and set aside.
Melt butter in a large pan and add cocoa.
Stir in the water and shortening.
Bring these four ingredients to a boil and remove from heat.
Stir in flour and sugar.
Mix the sour cream and baking soda together and add to cake mixture along with the eggs. Bake for 30 minutes until done to touch (springs back slightly when touched).

title: swiss baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain corn and mix all ingredients and 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with oleo and 1/4 cup cheese.
Sprinkle over corn.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla and brown sugar.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add chocolate chips, Rice Krispies, oatmeal, walnuts and coconut.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook onion in butter in microwave until tender.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wine baked fish
directions: Bake fish in wine and margarine at 350° for 7 minutes, until done.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 1.

title: beef jerky
directions: Thaw meat just enough to cut it into very thin strips.

Mix remaining ingredients to make a marinade. Soak the meat strips in the marinade in the refrigerator for 8 hours, stirring every hour. Drain the meat strips and place on trays in a food dehydrator. Dry until brittle. Meat will bend but not break when dry and should have no soft spots.
It may be stored at room temperature for about 1 week; for longer storage, keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pumpkin spice roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes (until foamy).
Gradually add sugar, stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients and fold in (do not use mixer).
Coat large cookie sheet with Pam, spread mixture in pan and top with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on (powdered sugar) towel (don't let cool in pan).
Roll towel and cake together, let cook, unroll, remove towel, spread on filling, roll back up and chill.

title: lazy cook's cabbage un-rolls
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Layer in pan:
cabbage, meat and rice. Top with tomato juice or tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup. Bake covered 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 2 teaspoons sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center.
Add peel, 1/3 cup orange juice and milk.
Stir just until dough clings together.

title: zucchini linguine cuisineyhouston, texas
directions: Cut squash and zucchini in julienne (small sticks).
Heat butter and oil in a large fry pan or casserole dish.
Add the garlic and cook over medium heat until opaque.
Add the squash, zucchini and basil and cook about 7 minutes or until soft, but be careful not to overcook!
Meanwhile, boil the pasta (linguine) in a large pot until al dente.
Drain and toss with squash mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan on top.

title: quick fudge
directions: Combine milk, chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla.
Heat on a low flame until chips are completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, small amounts at a time.
Add pecans and continue to work candy until it is a very thick consistency. Spread in a buttered dish.
Refrigerate a couple of hours to set.

title: puppy chow
directions: Sift powdered sugar into a large paper bag.
Empty cereal into large mixing bowl.
Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour melted mixture over cereal and toss to coat well.
Pour cereal into paper bag, roll down top and shake well.
Enjoy!

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Work butter or Crisco until creamy.
Add brown sugar and, when well blended, add egg.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and a little salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well and add nut meats.
Pack in a small bread pan, or form into a roll and chill in refrigerator.
