Cut off as needed and bake 8 minutes in a hot (400°) oven.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Use a teaspoon to form balls of the batter.
These may be any size you choose bite sized is best.
Place on cookie sheet and cool until firm.
Meanwhile, melt the chocolate morsels in a deep container such as a two-cup glass measure.
When balls of batter are formed, dip each and coat completely with chocolate.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet. Refrigerate or freeze.
Should be stored in sealed container. Great frozen!
Yields approx. 70 candies.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Saute bacon or sausage until partially cooked.
Add onions and cook until tender, but not brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg and milk; mix well.
Add bacon, onions and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: amaretto
directions: Dissolve sugar and coffee in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients when cool.

title: chocolate-zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar in bowl until light.
Stir in zucchini and cooled chocolate.
Mix in combined dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: health cookies
directions: Mix butter, honey and vanilla.
Mix other ingredients and then add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: ham and asparagus roll-ups
directions: Roll individual stalks of asparagus inside individual slices of ham.
Cut across each stalk, making each roll up into 2 or 3 pieces.
(Shorter stalks should be cut only once, into 2 pieces). As you make each cut, pin the ham to the asparagus with a toothpick.
Makes an appetizer or party finger food to feed about 12 people.

title: california pound cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients (sift together).
Do not use mixer; mix with wooden spoon.
Add oil, pineapple and egg yolks; mix well.
Add egg whites; mix well.
Put in funnel cake pan (spray with Pam).
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for approximately 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: iced pecans
directions: Line baking sheet with foil.
Butter the foil.
In a thick skillet, melt margarine; add sugar and mix well.
Add nuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 9 minutes or until sugar melts and turns to a rich brown color.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Cool; break into small pieces.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cut steak or roast into small pieces.
Brown and simmer meat in a skillet.
When almost done, add chopped tomato, peppers and onion.
Pour in flour until well mixed.
Add garlic salt, salt and 1 cup of water.
Let simmer until it becomes creamy gravy.
Fill tortillas with mixture.
Fold them (toothpicks help them stay closed).
Fry in oil in a skillet.
Garnish each with shredded lettuce, guacamole and sour cream.
A meal in itself.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out and cut with cutter; put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: shaker cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick, about 3 minutes.
Continue beating and add sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir in coconut, oats and chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
(Pie will be very dark.)
Cool completely before serving (leave the house if neccessary).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
This comes from the California and Hawaii Sugar Company.

title: marvell's chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake at 325°.
Do not overcook.

title: ranell's spiced tea
directions: Tie spices in a bag.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until spices are as strong as you like them.

title: lasagna(no cottage cheese)
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheeses.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Put layer of noodles in a 9 x 12-inch pan and alternate sauce, noodles, Swiss cheese and Mozzarella cheese, ending with this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with spatula after it sits 15 minutes.

title: irish apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, yolks, butter and lemon rind.
Divide into 2 parts; press 1 part into greased 9
x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Mix applesauce, cinnamon and cloves; spread on top.
Spread (crumble) other part of mix on top.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chili pie casserole(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Spread 2 cups Fritos in greased baking dish.
Arrange onion and half of cheese on Fritos.
Pour chili over onion and cheese. Top with remaining cheese, green pepper and 1 cup of Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly and onion is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crisp nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add next 2 ingredients and then add flour and nuts to the mixture.
Make into rolls and chill in refrigerator, then bake on an ungreased pan.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Fry chicken breasts until tender.
Dice in small pieces.
Mix sour cream and both soups together.
Place diced chicken in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Crumble crackers over top of mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers, then pour melted over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries dredged in flour, just until mixed, then add blueberries.
Fill muffin tins a little over halfway full and sprinkle about 1/4 teaspoon sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour and brown in oil in large Dutch oven. Add onions and garlic; cook until vegetables are softened.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients (except tomatoes, potatoes and carrots); bring to a boil, cover and simmer one hour.
Add tomatoes, potatoes and carrots and simmer 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yield:
8 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: angel food jello cake
directions: Take strawberries out of freezer and leave on counter to thaw. Dissolve Jell-O in water in large mixer bowl.
Mix on medium speed for about 5 minutes (until foamy).
Spoon strawberries into slightly thickened Jell-O.
Pour strawberry/Jell-O mixture onto cake.
Let it set in refrigerator for about 2 to 3 hours, then serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Melt the baking chocolate and margarine; stir well.
Mix in the sugar; stir.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and flour; stir.
Add nuts and 1/2 bag of the chocolate chips to mix.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 bag of chocolate chips on top of unbaked brownies.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes.

title: butternut chewies
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy in a large bowl with electric mixer.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy.

title: pork steaks and dressing
directions: Brown steaks in a small amount of fat, then season with salt and pepper.
Add onion to drippings until light brown.
Add bread, corn, sage, salt and paprika to taste.
Place stuffing in 9 x 13-inch pan and place steaks on top.
Cover tightly and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: arbitrator
directions: Serve in chimney glass.

title: best-ever turtles
directions: On a baking sheet, arrange pecan halves in sets of 3, laying 2 side by side and 1 across the top; set aside. Combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup whipping cream in a heavy saucepan; heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches a full boil. Slowly add remaining cream and butter; heat until mixture reaches the soft boil stage or 240° on a candy thermometer. Cool; spoon a desired amount of caramel mixture on top of each set of pecans. Let set; dip in melted chocolate. Refrigerate to harden. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening and peanut butter until well blended; add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Drop batter in greased muffin pans and bake at 350° until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: basic three-bean salad
directions: Combine the beans.
In a large bowl, toss the beans with the onion and green pepper.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the mixture in the bowl.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender, not brown.
Stir in peas, milk, soup and pepper.
Boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix instant pudding, milk and vanilla ice cream in a large bowl with mixer.
Pour in baked graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a bowl. Add melted butter and mix well. Stir in eggs one at a time. Mix all the ingredients. Put in 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients. Drizzle over chicken.
Bake for one hour, basting every 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
This is great served over Uncle Ben's long grain and wild rice.

title: chocolate-butterscotch cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, remove from oven and prick holes in top of cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the cake.
Allow to cool.
Spread caramel topping on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Break up Heath candy bars and sprinkle over top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Dial 227-FAST.
Place order for a large pepperoni pizza.
Wait 30 minutes.
Open lid and serve.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill milk 24 hours.
Dissolve the jello and water; add honey, salt
and lemon juice.
When it is slightly congealed, beat milk until stiff and whip jello mixture into it.
Spread 1/2 of	wafer crumbs
in large pan, 10 x 13 1/2-inches.
Pour jello mixture over top and cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill 3 hours.
Serves 15 to 18 people.

title: gabe's venison stew
directions: Cut venison into serving pieces.
Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Coat venison with flour mixture.
Heat bacon fat in skillet and brown venison on both sides.
Add celery and onions and saute until limp.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes. Cover and cook on medium heat for two hours or until meat is tender.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: mama's party mints
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 3/4 inch balls and cross with a fork.
Lay out to dry.
Store in airtight containers.
Omit vanilla flavoring and add a few drops of wintergreen or peppermint flavoring if you like.
Tint pink for peppermint and green for wintergreen.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine and mix salts.
Pour over cereals and nuts. Bake for 2 hours at 250°, stirring occasionally.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Serve over cream cheese on crackers.

title: corn chip pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with crushed corn chips and grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese melts.
To make it more spicy, salsa or Mexican cheese may be added.

title: clark's famous mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan (a turkey roasting pan works fine).
Bring it to a slow boil on medium heat.
Reduce to a simmer.
Cook 3 to 5 hours, until liquid barely covers mushrooms. Serve hot in a chafing dish or crock-pot.
These may be refrigerated or frozen.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Cream flour and butter.
Add to egg mixture.
Add other ingredients as listed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake in layers at 375° until done. Put together with Japanese Fruitcake Filling.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: This is a good casserole to fix if you are expecting a lot of guests.

title: ground meat and sausage dip
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add Velveeta, picante sauce and soup.
Serve with large Fritos.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Combine grated zucchini, sugar and grated oranges.
Pour into large roasting or baking dish and bake for 3 hours at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Add cherries and bake another 1/2 hour. Pack in hot jars with hot lids.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: cauliflower slaw
directions: Put cauliflower in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cauliflower. Marinate 24 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into dish lined with vanilla wafers.
Add more vanilla wafers around edge and on top for garnish, if desired.
Chill until pudding is set.

title: corn casserole 1
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° in a shallow 2-quart casserole, approximately 1 hour or until firm.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put in a flat 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine; add almonds and crushed corn flakes.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut or mash artichoke hearts. Add green chili peppers; mix well. Then add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese; mix thoroughly. Place in baking dish. Put in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes (or until cheese is melted). Enjoy!

title: hot caramel sundae
directions: In top of double boiler, over simmering water, melt butter, caramels and evaporated milk, stirring until smooth.
Store in a covered container, refrigerated; to use within 30 days, rewarming sauce over hot water or in a microwave oven on Defrost to spoon over ice cream.

title: alcapurrias(stuffed green bananas)
directions: In a mortar, crush peppercorns, garlic, salt and oregano. Blend in olive oil and vinegar.
Add seasoning to the beef and mix. Brown seasoned beef in a skillet over high heat (no extra oil is necessary).
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in tomato sauce and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, remove meat to a bowl and set aside.
Peel bananas and plantain, cut in half.
Grate the bananas and plantain, using the grating dish of a food processor or a hand held shredder.
Mix in a bowl with the achiote; then mash with a fork or potato masher.
Spread some of the banana-plantain mix in the palm of your hand (keep palms wet while doing this).
With your fingers, make a small nest in the center of the mix in your palm and stuff with about a spoonful of the beef filling.
Cover the filling with more mix and shape into a cylinder of croquette.
Repeat until filling and bananas are used up. Deep-fry in very hot oil (375°) until golden brown (about 4 minutes each).
Remove and drain on absorbent paper towels.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

In large mixer bowl, beat butter, shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg. Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet. With fork dipped in sugar, flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in buttered dish.
Cover with cut up chicken. Combine mayonnaise, soup and curry powder and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with cracker crumbs; sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hunt burgers
directions: Form beef into 8 thin hamburger patties.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay cheese on 4 patties.
Cover with remaining patties.
Pinch edges together to enclose the cheese completely. Brown on one side in hot oil in skillet.
Turn and pour tomato sauce over them.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot with the delicious pan gravy.

title: mr. brock's halftime heroes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat and barbecue sauce; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Fill rolls with meat mixture and top with cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: corn soup
directions: Put the milk on to boil in a double boiler.
Add the corn cobs from which the corn has been removed.
Cover and cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Remove the cobs.
Add the corn.
Cook 20 minutes more and press through a puree sieve.
Rub the butter and flour together. Add to the soup and stir continually until it thickens.
Beat the yolks of the eggs and put them in the tureen.
Add gradually the hot soup.
Season and serve.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Step 1:
Blend together flour, margarine and nuts for crust. Bake 15 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry nut fudge cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and buttermilk.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: char's grandma's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except brown sugar, in a large bowl until blended.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: truck patch dinner
directions: Arrange one layer of bacon on bottom of roasting pan or casserole dish.
Add a layer of raw hamburger.
Add a layer of sliced potatoes, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; add a layer of peas and carrots and rest of bacon.
Return to oven and bake 45 minutes.

title: rocky mountain rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; chill.
Season to taste.

title: raspberry walnut torte
directions: Blend well flour, powdered sugar and soft margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Drain raspberries. Reserve liquid for sauce.
Spoon berries over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Beat eggs and sugar in small bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour over raspberries and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream with sauce over both ice ice cream and dessert.

title: icebox cucumber pickle
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bring to a rolling boil and cool. Layer sliced cucumbers and onion in layers in gallon jar. Pour mixture over. Chill approximately 3 days. Stir occasionally. Will keep in refrigerator months! May add peppers, celery, zucchini or yellow squash. Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken with stuffing
directions: Place chicken in a greased slow cooker. Top with soup.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Add butter to spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Butter a pie plate and press mixture all around bottom and edges, forming a crust.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and green pepper and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sauce, sugar, salt and garlic salt.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together oleo (melted), flour and nuts.
Pat down into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat together pudding and milk, 1 to 2 minutes until mixed well.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes. Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Place 1/2 cup margarine in slices on aluminum foil.
Put in potatoes, peppers, onions and creamed corn.
Put remaining margarine on top.
Wrap and seal.
Vent with fork holes.
Place on a grill and cook 30 to 45 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: microwave garlic shrimp with capellini
directions: In an 8-inch square baking dish, combine the garlic and oil. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add the broth and paprika. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add shrimp and lemon juice. Toss to combine.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 1 minute.

title: easy cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pie filling in pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the ingredients.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Put butter on top of this.
Bake at 350° or until lightly brown on top, 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, chop apples with peeling, pecans and oranges.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add sugar.
When sugar is dissolved, add to pecans, cranberries and fruit mixture. Chill until set.
"This is good to make ahead of time and keep in the refrigerator."

title: german baked brisket
directions: Brown meat in heavy casserole at 450° for about 25 minutes on each side. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Reduce heat to 325° and pour mixture over meat and cover casserole with foil.
Bake 3 hours or until tender, basting occasionally. Slice brisket thinly.
Spoon over pan juices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer squash spice cake
directions: Sift together all the dry ingredients.
Beat the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Beat in the dry ingredients.
Stir in the grated squash.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: new orleans baked bananas with orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 4 pieces of foil approximately 4 x 6-inches. Peel bananas; cut in half lengthwise and place each on foil.
In a small bowl, mix orange juice, orange rind, honey and vanilla.
Spoon over bananas.
Top each half with a piece of butter.
Fold foil, then place on baking sheet up to this point, then above steps can be done ahead.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
If bananas are ripe, 5 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream jello
directions: Mix and pour into a greased mold.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine both ingredients. Serve with apples or any fruit of your choice.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix
beans,
chili
powder,
garlic
powder
and
onion flakes, mashing together well. Brown hamburger;
drain and mix with first mixture.
Place	in
corn tortilla shells.
Roll up and place in pan.
Pour
chili	over,
then cover with cheese. Serve with taco sauce, lettuce and tomatoes (chopped).
I like a little sour cream or a guacamole salad.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Sift flour.
Add sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly and knead.
Cover with damp cloth and put in refrigerator.

title: amaretto chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, Amaretto, butter and salt. Add chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: all-in-one tuna casserole
directions: A good ol' 1950's style, high cholesterol, fatty, salt-laden, delicious, simple breakfast!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together with mixer (may be lumpy).
Add taco seasoning mix with spoon and stir.
Spread the mix on large cookie sheet.
Add lettuce, chopped tomato, cheese and black olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: Fry sausage, browning evenly.
Drain, leaving about 3 tablespoons of the liquid.
Put in cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fry 6 minutes, turning often.
Serve hot.

title: roasted pecans(very good)
directions: Melt oil and butter on large cookie sheet or broiler tray. (Cannot be sideless as the butter-oil mixture will run out.) Sprinkle with salt. Spread pecans over pan in single thickness and stir to coat them with butter-oil mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Add more salt, if necessary.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice, water, and salt in saucepan and bring to boil over high heat.
Turn down low, cover, simmer 14 minutes.
Stir in milk and cook uncovered 20 - 30 minutes until all milk is absorbed; do not boil.
Stir occasionally.
Stir frequently towards end of cooking.
Stir in nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Stir some of the hot mixture into eggs.
Return mixture to saucepan.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 1 1/2 qt. glass baking dish.
Place dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 300 degrees for 50 - 60 minutes. Pudding stiffens as it cools.
Sift 2 tsp. of powdered sugar on top (if desired).
Serve warm.
Serves:

title: mom's white lemon cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add lemon extract and grape juice.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to mixture.
Gradually add 3 cups of the flour.
Save the remainder for dredging the fruit.
Mix soda in the warm water and add to the mixture.
Blend well.
Dredge the fruit and nuts in the remaining flour, then add to the batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Makes 1 large tube pan and a large loaf.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 2 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Pour spaghetti sauce into Dutch oven.
Add beef broth, 2 cups water, celery, sugar, salt, beef and onions; bring to a boil.
Simmer 45 minutes. Add vegetables and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kaylene's cookies
directions: Mix eggs and 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Mix in half of cake mix. Blend well.
Blend in remaining cake mix; batter will become very sticky.

title: chicken with mild white wine and butter sauce
directions: Saute spring onions and chicken pieces in butter in a deep skillet until chicken is no longer pink.
Add wine and 1 cup water and simmer over low-medium heat.
Add sliced mushrooms and continue to simmer for 10 minutes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add carrots; sprinkle with salt. Add
honey	and
toss until all are well coated.
Cover and bake at 350° until carrots are hot.
Do not brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Boil ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours, until some of the moisture cooks off.
Pour 2 or 3 cups slowly into blender or food processor; process on high speed until smooth.
Pour into freezer containers, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Freeze.
This makes an excellent base for chili and pasta sauces.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs well. Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix well. Pour into greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Great with ham.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery for a few minutes, until softened. Combine the next five ingredients in a bowl.
Add onion and celery.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place a layer of broccoli and chicken.
Pour mushroom soup over.
Layer until you have used up ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yellow squash
directions: Wash and cut off ends of squash.
Put drippings in frying pan. Add squash, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, slowly as steam tenders squash. Remove cover from pan and allow excess water to slowly dry up. Remove from heat and serve.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: broiled open-faced sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, tomato, mushrooms, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion powder and tarragon. Spread half of the mixture on one side of each waffle.
Place waffles, spread side up, on rack of unheated broiler pan.
Broil for 5 to 7 minutes or until spread is bubbly.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press on bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
In bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour in spring-form pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, until center is set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick.

title: millionaires pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in graham cracker crust; refrigerate. May also be frozen.
Yield:
2 large 9-inch or 4 small 8-inch, baked.

title: alaskan clam chowder
directions: Pare and cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes, place in pot and enough water to cover.
Cook over medium heat until tender, not so much to lose shape or "mealy."
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch cubes, fry until golden brown and lightly crisp, drain on towel, same some of the grease.
Peel, slice and cube onions, fry in bacon fat until soft and golden.
Lift out and add to potatoes.
Season with salt and a generous amount of freshly ground pepper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash together potatoes, half and half, cinnamon, brown sugar, salt and egg until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows and walnuts on top.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: lo-fat company casserole
directions: Layer corn, noodles, diced ham and peas.
Mix sour cream, cheese, margarine, milk and soup and spread on top of layered ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with onions.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: chess pie
directions: Using mixer, beat butter until creamy. Add sugar and eggs; blend thoroughly. Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: "crock-pot supper"(smothered round steak)
directions: Place 1/4 cup flour and seasonings in bottom of pot.
Stir meat into pot.
Layer onion, green pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms. Add soy sauce and molasses.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low.
Put green beans on top.
Do not stir.
Thicken to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate marshmallow peanut butter cake
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, yogurt and mayo; blend with mixer until smooth.
Add soup, chestnuts and garlic; stir in spinach.
Chill 2 hours.

title: kraut and sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 2-inch lengths and butterfly each piece.
Put cut edge down in heavy frying pan and cook over low heat until nicely browned.
Add kraut and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix oranges and pineapple and strain well.
Mix fruit with dry jello and cottage cheese last.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Do night before and it will be set nice.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast mixture, water, oil, salt and sugar.
Mix well. Work in flour.
Place in a covered container out of the drafts for 10 to 12 hours.
Knead and put in a bowl to rise until double. Knead and make into rolls or can be made into loaves.
Put in pans and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and bacon dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy and add rest of ingredients. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: low-fat spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, then place in a large pot. Slice mushrooms, then saute in a small amount of olive oil along with a good amount of chopped garlic. Place in pot with meat. Add the tomato sauce and tomato paste. Add dill seed.
Add oregano, thyme and basil to your taste. Simmer for 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: sweet and sour wiener bites
directions: Mix the mustard and jelly in chafing dish or double boiler. Slice franks, diagonally, in bite-sized pieces.
Add to sauce and heat thoroughly.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Mix in pan and bring to a boil.
Allow to cool and add one large bottle or 1 can of chilled Coca-Cola.
Let thicken and then add 1 can crushed pineapple and 1 cup pecans.
Chill.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Gradually add whipping cream to the Marshmallow Creme in saucepan, mixing until well blended.
Add chocolate chips.
Over low heat, cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth.
Stir in liqueur.
Transfer to fondue pot.
Serve warm.

title: tuna braid
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. On cookie sheet, lay out crescent rolls pinched together to make one long roll. Turn mixing bowl tuna mixture onto dough. Form long loaf keeping enough edge to turn up on sides and ends.
Add 3-4 thick slices of Provolone Cheese on top of the tuna loaf.
Bring dough up on sides and ends just enough to cover outer edges of cheese. Should look like loaf. Ready to bake at 350° for 20 minutes or till light golden brown.

title: chicken salad sandwich
directions: In bowl, combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: carol's banana pudding
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk and pudding mix together using mixer. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Garnish with cookie crumbs.
Chill.

title: canadian bacon waldorf salad
directions: Whisk sour cream, mayonnaise, juice concentrate, lemon juice and ginger in a large bowl.
Stir in apple, bacon, celery, oranges and pecans.
Add sweet potatoes.
Serve over lettuce.
Delicious!

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased pan. Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and add milk and cheese.
Stir over low heat until mixture thickens.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Melt oleo.
Add
onions
and
bell peppers.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion soup and chicken soup.
Heat until mixed well. Stir in raw rice and shrimp.
Mix well.
Cover with lid.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Take
out
and
stir and put back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix thoroughly and keep covered in refrigerator.
Serve with ham or, for an appetizer, spoon over cube of cream cheese and serve with crackers.
Makes 5 cups.

title: easy cream cheese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Place cream cheese on serving dish.
Pour chili sauce over it. Serve with any crackers.

title: sicilian frittata
directions: In a large skillet, saute peppers, potatoes and onion in olive oil just until onion turns transparent.
Add salt and pepper to beaten eggs and pour eggs evenly over skillet contents.
Keep the heat medium to low.
With spatula, lift the frittata gently as it cooks, letting the runny eggs spill gently to the bottom of the skillet.
When it starts to firm up, but is still uncooked on top, take a large plate and slide the frittata onto it.
Then, turn the skillet over the plate to cover it and while holding tightly to the plate, flip it over back into the skillet so the other side can finish cooking.
Cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes, but be careful not to burn the bottom.
Slice as you would a pie.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, margarine and milk in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it reaches a rolling boil. Cook 10 minutes. Be sure you can't stir the bubbles down while timing.
Remove from stove.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy and thick.
Pour into a buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put in 2 quart casserole or 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
If refrigerated before baking, bake covered 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6-8.

title: johnny mozetti
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Add other ingredients and heat until cheese is melted and serve as a casserole.

title: mom's rolls
directions: Mix together warm water, sugar and salt.
Add yeast.
Stir in egg, shortening and flour.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover tightly.
May be kept in refrigerator up to 3 days, but knead down when rises.

title: chicken fried cube steaks
directions: Dip steaks into egg mixture, then flour and egg and then flour again.
Put steaks into skillet and fry until golden brown (about 5 minutes).
Turn steaks over and fry other side.
Excellent with a milk gravy, served on mashed potatoes, Southern style black-eyed peas and baked beans.
Delicious!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together well.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into one large or two small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers of choice.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature at least 24 hours.
Heat oven to 200°.
Butter cookie sheet.
Drain pumpkin seeds; place on prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn of oven; leave in oven overnight or until oven has cooled completely.
Makes 2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt 1 stick butter with cheese. Put 1/2 broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of the cheese over.
Add remaining broccoli and cheese.
Melt 1 stick butter with cracker crumbs sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Crack eggs into a bowl and add a little milk. Use wire whisk or fork to beat eggs. Scramble eggs in skillet. When eggs are done, take away from heat. Take flour tortilla and place a spoonful of eggs. Add little cheese and roll up. Place in baking dish, 9 x 13 size. Pour enchilada sauce over the burritos and sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until cheese has melted. Can serve with sour cream or salsa.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt, pepper and paprika. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and melted butter.
Place chicken in an oblong dish.
Marinate at least one hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Mix brown sugar with pineapple; pour mixture over chicken and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Mix in other ingredients. Let set in fridge.
When set, mix 1 box vanilla instant pudding according to directions.
Pour over jello mixture; let set. Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Use a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: dropped mincemeat cookies
directions: Drop in pan.
Cook for about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick and easy cream of potato soup
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add 1 cup of cream to water and vegetables.
Next, take any brand of instant potatoes and add to the soup ingredients until thick as you desire.
Serve hot.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator.
Great for shrimp or other fish.

title: red velvet christmas cake
directions: Cream the Crisco.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat.
Put cocoa and salt in cake coloring and make a paste.
Add to mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk (alternate).
Put soda in vinegar; add to mixtures.
Mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch layers for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into bite size balls
and place in 13 x9-inch pan.

title: oriental shrimp casserole
directions: Saute shrimp lightly in oleo for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add celery, onion, mushrooms, water chestnuts, almonds and half the noodles. Pour into a medium casserole and cover with remaining noodles. Mix the soup, milk and soy sauce.
Pour over the noodles. Sprinkle with paprika and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add alternately the buttermilk, flour and salt.
Add chocolate in boiling water.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar
and
cream.
Cook
Remove from heat and add
salt and butter.
Beat until it begins to grain. Stir in vanilla and nuts and pour into buttered pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Add fruit and pour 1/2 of mixture into mold or oblong pan and set firmly.
Pour sour cream on set jello and remaining jello mixture and return to refrigerator until firmly set.

title: spaghetti testaverde carbonara
directions: Cook pasta until al dente and set aside.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and cook through in a frying pan about 5 minutes. Whisk the egg yolks and combine half the Parmesan and set aside. Now reheat your frying pan with medium heat.
Using large spoons, combine the noodles and bacon.
Remove the frying pan from heat and immediately pour in the egg mixture, stirring quickly.
The heat of the pasta will cook the egg and thicken the sauce.
Serve immediately topped with the rest of the Parmesan.
(Some people like to add some cooked peas to the mixture.)

title: new year's cookies
directions: Mix milk, butter, eggs, salt, sugar and vanilla together. Add yeast, which has been softened in the lukewarm water. Stir well. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Let raise. Pinch off portions, about the size of an egg and fry in deep fat. Drain well. Roll in sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Slowly add sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add flavorings. Sift flour and sift again.
Add baking powder to last sift.
Add flavor alternately with milk.
Start with flour and end with flour. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar, syrup and salt. Stir in peanuts.
Cook at High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook at High for 4 minutes.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Cook at High for 1 minute.
Add the baking soda and stir quickly (mixture will be foamy.) Immediately pour onto a lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Saute lobster lightly if raw.
Dice; set aside.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes.
Blend in dry clam broth.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Add all but cream; mix well.
Add cream; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Line bottom of deep bowl (glass looks best) with layer of sponge cake, split and spread with raspberry jam.
If desired, soak with sherry.
Then add a layer of fruit (preferably raspberries, well drained).
Add layer of custard or vanilla pudding.
Make a Jell-O and when ready set, pour over firm custard.
Top with fresh whipped cream.
Decorate as desired with glace cherries, angelica, grated chocolate, etc.

title: herbed chicken in lime juice
directions: Marinate chicken in lime juice for at least an hour.
Dip chicken in melted butter and put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with the mixed herbs and bake for 1 hour (or until done and browned) in 350° oven.
Baste frequently.

title: spicy sausage-potato casserole
directions: Use vegetable oil to grease a shallow 2-quart casserole. Arrange next 4 ingredients in a casserole and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Beat together next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over first mixture; reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Drizzle with sauce.
Slice Mozzarella cheese and then cut in 1-inch pieces.
Arrange on a casserole.
Bake for 10 additional minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into squares for easy melting in medium bowl. Add can of Ro-Tel.
Microwave for 5 minutes; stir.
Depending on your microwave, continue to melt and stir at 1 minute intervals until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and green pepper; set aside.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Stir-fry frozen broccoli, carrots and water chestnuts until tender.
Mix ground beef mixture with rice and vegetables.
Serve hot.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese. Mix well.
Pack into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours or until thoroughly cooked.
May top meat loaf with Cheddar cheese during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: large cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese and eggs sit at room temperature 3 hours. Beat cream cheese and sugar together; add eggs one at a time and blend thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Do not open. Leave in oven for 1 hour.
Open and let cool 2 hours.
Use any topping desired.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine salt, curry powder, pineapple juice and 1/2 cup water; bring to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Let return to boil and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until tender.
Cook peas 5 minutes and drain.
Combine with other ingredients (except almonds).
Before serving, add almonds.
Serve with pineapple rings and your favorite crackers or muffins.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Assemble above ingredients in order given in layers in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat on low until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Save 1 1/2 cups crumbs for topping.
Use remaining crumbs for crust and press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Spoon pie filling evenly over crust and sprinkle with marshmallows, then remaining crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until light brown; do not overbake.
Cool. Cut into bars.
(We like to top with ice cream for a great tasting treat.)

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; put into fridge overnight.
Add the bananas, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Mix warm water and yeast; set aside.
Put in bowl the milk and 1/2 cup water and heat (do not boil).
Add lard, salt and sugar. Add flour to thickness of pancake dough.
Let cool to lukewarm. Add more flour and yeast mixture.
Mix well and let rise double. Knead and cut; let rise again and fry in deep hot fat.

title: chocolate coconut haystacks
directions: Then drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Saute onion in oleo, then add soups, peppers and chicken while this is heated together.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with tortilla chips; pour meat mixture on chips.
Top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Fast!

title: caribbean lime chicken
directions: Using a swivel-bladed vegetable peeler, remove the peel from half of the lime and set aside.
Juice the lime and set aside. Add the lime peel to the lime juice, along with the rum or orange juice, garlic, ginger and red pepper sauce.
Add the chicken, tossing to coat well.

Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight, turning the chicken in the marinade several times. Lightly coat a heavy 12-inch skillet with the nonstick cooking spray and set over moderate heat for 30 seconds.
Add the chicken, reserving the marinade, and cook about 2 1/2 minutes on each side. Transfer to a platter.
Raise the heat under the skillet to high and boil the sauce, uncovered, until slightly thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Return the chicken to the skillet and heat through for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove the cinnamon stick, arrange the chicken and sauce in a serving dish and garnish with the banana slices, if you like.
Serves 4.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Blend butter and cream with seasonings.
Place chicken breasts on individual pieces of heavy foil.
Top with butter and cream mixture.
Fold edges tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot in foil.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add ingredients in layers in the order listed.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.
Good with ice cream on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Add oatmeal and raisins. Beat eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased pan.
Makes about 30 large cookies.
Raisins may be omitted and add chocolate or butterscotch chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: italian sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Brown sausage, onion, garlic and chopped stems in oil.
Drain well.
Mix with bread crumbs, egg and cheese.
Stuff mushrooms full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with extra Parmesan.

title: brittle cookies
directions: Place a layer of foil in an 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan and layer crackers over foil.
In a saucepan, combine butter and sugar. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes or until crackers float.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate morsels over top of crackers.

title: big mama's cheesecake
directions: Take softened cream cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and beat until smooth.
Taste to see if you want to add more lemon juice.
Pour into crust and refrigerate overnight.
Top with your favorite pie filling or each plain.

title: cheeseburger turnover(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Thirty minutes before serving, preheat oven to 425°.
In skillet, combine meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Saute 5 minutes or until meat is brown.
On pastry board with lightly floured rolling pin, roll 2 of the biscuits slightly overlapping into 6 x 5-inch ovals.
On half of oval, pile with tablespoon of meat mixture; top with half slice of cheese.
Fold other half of biscuit over cheese and meat.
Moisten with water on edges; pinch together.
Prick top of turnover with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until brown, on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, eggs and melted margarine.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with or without whipped cream.
Pie should be chewy.

title: baked tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Crumble up tuna.
Mix all ingredients and stir the milk in last.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole and pour in.
Cover for awhile until it comes to a boil, then uncover and bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4.

title: flavored cream cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth and creamy. Add your favorite fruit.

title: leftover beef
directions: Saute 1 small sliced onion and celery in butter about 10 minutes (lid on pot).
Stir in contents of brown gravy mix, water and beef.
(Water must be cold.)
Cook, stirring, until mixture comes to boil and thickens.
Serve on rice.
(Mixture will thicken quickly.)

title: bruschetta(appetizer)
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Remove pulp and seeds.
Dice tomatoes into small pieces.
Chop basil and mix with tomatoes and salt.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Boil for 30 minutes the above ingredients.
Coat the chicken as if you are going to fry.
Place in roaster.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 425° for 1 hour or until chicken is well done.

title: canned venison
directions: Pack venison into hot jars.
Place a clove of garlic and a pinch of salt into each jar.
Secure lid.
Place in pressure canner on 10 pounds for 90 minutes.
When ready to eat pour into frying pan with a little grease and a chopped onion.
Season to taste. Very good!

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into 2-quart dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir twice for even cooking.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix water, bouillon cubes and onion.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add broccoli and noodles.
When noodles are tender, add remaining ingredients. Simmer and stir until well mixed.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Good with fish or meat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and eggs well.
Add all other ingredients, but butter.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Use mixer to mix butter in well.
Pour in one 10-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 3 drops of yellow food coloring. Suggested uses:
coleslaw, potato salad, deviled eggs and sandwich spread.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked chicken and yellow rice
directions: In a large bowl, mix rice, seasoning package and soups.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Place onion slices on top and pour melted margarine over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chesapeake linguine(serves 2)
directions: In a skillet, cook the garlic and scallions in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, until garlic is pale golden.
Add the tomatoes, basil and red pepper flakes and cook the mixture for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper and stir in the capers.

title: spicy fries
directions: Slice potatoes into finger-like shapes.
Place in baking dish. Add oil.
Mix all spices and sprinkle over sliced potatoes.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean-water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans according to directions.
Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine.
Sprinkle in flour, then slowly add grated cheese, Tabasco sauce, milk, salt and pepper.
Let thicken; add water chestnuts.
Mix beans with sauce and turn into greased casserole.
Sprinkle onions or almonds on top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in large skillet.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans and soak in water overnight (at least 12 hours). Cook over medium heat for about 1 hour in deep pot.
Chop onion, garlic and green pepper.
Saute all 3 in frying pan with olive oil until tender, then add to beans.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, bay leaf and sugar.
Cook over low heat for an additional 1 hour.
Add vinegar and white wine.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender and desired thickness.
Serve over white rice and sprinkle with chopped onions.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cover and chill 8 hours.

title: basic white bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in
sugar,
salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in
warm
water in warmed bowl.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and
cups
flour.
Attach
dough hooks, turn speed to 2 (medium) for 2 minutes or well blended; continuing on speed 2, add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough clings to hook
about 3 minutes.
Knead on speed 2 for 7 to 10 minutes
longer
or
until
dough
is
smooth
and elastic.
Dough will be
slightly
sticky to the touch.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let
rise
in
warm place, free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: Combine pepper, salt and
paprika
in
hot
water.
Let stand 10
minutes.
Add
peanut oil to mixture.
Wash and dry turkey; rub peanut oil mixture inside and around all sides of paper grocery
sack
(type
used
in grocery store).
Rub oil inside and outside of turkey.
Place turkey in sack.
Fold end over and staple securely.
Bake at 325°.
Lower temperature to 225°
and cook all night.
Twelve hours is sufficient for any size turkey if baking on low temperature.

title: ribbon sandwich
directions: Blend all this together, drain off all juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together with 3 blocks of cream cheese and 1 or 2 tbsp. mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stack on 3 pieces of bread; trim off edge and cut with electric knife like finger sandwiches.

title: shoe peg corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and season with salt and black pepper.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 roll Ritz crackers on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and taco seasoning in plastic bag.
Shake chicken a few pieces at a time in seasoning and flour.
Pour oil or melted butter in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan and turn to coat.
Take chicken from pan and roll in crushed chips and return to pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: pork chop dinner in a skillet
directions: Fry pork
chops
in
electric skillet for 10 minutes on each side.
Add
enough water to just cover chops and cook for 20 minutes at 250° with cover.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery, onion, salt
and
pepper.
Cover
and cook another 20 minutes. Add cheese,
cover
and
cook
minutes
more.
Stir before serving.
Serve with biscuits or hard rolls.

title: string beans supreme
directions: Pray.
Into casserole, add drained string beans.
Add golden mushroom soup, water and bacon bits.
Stir until mixed together. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese to top.
Bake until cheese is golden brown.

title: barbecue weenies
directions: Cook in a crock-pot or slowly on stove.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 3 medium or 2 large loaves.

title: grandma's noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles; drain and combine with melted butter.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks with sugar. Add to egg yolk mixture, noodles, sour cream, vanilla extract, milk and cottage cheese.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease pan generously with butter.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chess pies(makes 2)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Then pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit whip
directions: Beat cream until softly rounded peaks are formed.
Fold in fruit pulp, sugar and lemon juice carefully to retain lightness. Chill and serve cold.

title: sweet tooth delight(a layered frozen dessert)
directions: Take the Oreo cookies and separate cream from cookie.
Crush cookies; mix with the softened butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chili
directions: In a large skillet or pot, brown meat, onion and garlic. Add chili mix, chili powder, vinegar, hot sauce and tomato juice. Add beans, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: First layer in dish is the beans.
Second layer is ground beef and taco seasoning cooked together.
Third layer is nacho cheese dip.
Fourth layer is salsa or taco sauce.
Fifth layer is the cheese.
Cook about 20 minutes or until hot all the way through. Serve on chips.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Pour melted butter into mixture. Shape into logs.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler and dip the logs.
Cool on wax paper.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Layer each ingredient.
Serve with Ranch or buttermilk dressing.

title: icebox rolls(no kneading)
directions: To the 2 cups boiling water, add 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Let the mixture cool to lukewarm.
Soften the yeast cakes in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to the yeast. Stir this mixture into the first one.
Add eggs and 4 cups flour. Beat well.
Stir in 4 more cups of flour and mix well.
Cover the bowl and put in the refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Remove from the refrigerator and shape into a roll.
Place in a round pan and let rise 1 to 2 hours, until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Chop green onions, bell pepper and tomato in a medium size bowl.
Add cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Then season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Let chill 1 hour before serving.
The longer it sets the better it is.
Goes well with chips or Mexican casserole.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Chill.
Beat until foamy.
Add salad dressing and sugar.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
After cool, chop in small pieces.
Combine chicken, 1 cup broth you cooked it in, peas (not drained), Veg-All and cream of chicken soup.
In a separate mixing bowl, combine 1 stick of melted margarine, 1 cup flour or Bisquick and 1 cup milk and blend.
Pour batter mixture over chicken mixture in large baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400° until crust is golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6 people (may double for larger family).

title: no bake cookies
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together until stiff.
Fold in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Using teaspoon, place on aluminum cookie sheet in preheated 350° oven. Turn oven off and leave for 8 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix according to package.
Add corn.
Pour into 9-inch pie or square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven for approximately 3 minutes.

title: baked limas
directions: Cook lima beans in water for about 1 hour until skins begin to curl off, leave water on.
In baking dish combine meat, onion, syrup, sugars, salt and mustard (may also add a little ketchup). Add beans and cover with more water if needed (beans must be kept covered.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix ingredients and knead into a soft pliable dough.
Let rest 10 minutes under a warm bowl.
Divide the dough in half.
Roll out the dough on a floured surface to 1/8 or 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut out circles of dough, about 4 inches in diameter from the dough. Place a rounded tablespoon of filling to one side of each circle, then fold the dough over to make a half moon.
Carefully seal the edges by pinching together or crimping with the tines of a fork. Cook in 2 quarts boiling water.
Add only enough pierogi to the boiling water to make one layer.
Crowding makes them stick together.
Count cooking time after the water returns to boiling. About 4 to 6 minutes later the pierogi will float.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Serve drizzled with melted butter or Polish style, sprinkled with buttered bread crumbs.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook bacon and break into small pieces.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pixie frank's breakfast casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan as follows:
2 cups of the Rice Krispies, sausage, onion, rice and cheese.
Mix eggs and soup.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with the remaining 2 cups of Rice Krispies.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add butter and cream.
Mix until well combined. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with lightly sweetened whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat the eggs thoroughly. Beat in sugar. Stir in shortening. Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in mixture. Fry in deep fat at 370° to 380°.

title: beef or venison salami
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; refrigerate for 3 days, stirring well each day.
On the third day, mix the liquid smoke into meat.
Divide mix into 3 parts and roll into solid logs.
Wrap each roll in aluminum foil.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.

title: boneless chicken breast marsala
directions: Beat eggs with seasoning.
Dip meat in eggs first, then in flour or bread crumbs.
(If floured, put on wax paper and refrigerate to set.)
Brown on both sides and drain.
Saute for 10 minutes the following in butter or margarine:
garlic cloves, onion, peppers and mushrooms.
Remove from pan and set aside.
In same pan, add broth, bouillon cubes and Marsala wine.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put browned meat in pan and all vegetables.
Simmer for 5 minutes more.

title: fruit salad for a big group
directions: Freeze, thaw to a slush.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in refrigerator for 6 hours before serving.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Have frosting ready when cake comes out of oven.

title: chicken with stuffing
directions: Place chicken in a greased slow cooker. Top with soup in a bowl combine water, oleo and stuffing mix. Spoon over chicken. Cover and cook on low 4 hours or until chicken juices run clear.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer bread, cheese and ham. Combine eggs, mustard, milk, salt and pepper and pour over layered ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Stir together chocolate, milk and margarine over heat until margarine melts.
Let cool.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread crushed cookies, cover with ice cream, top with fudge sauce and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze for several hours before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, flour, sugar and egg yolks.
It's better to mix small amount of milk first and then add rest.
Cook until it starts to thicken, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla last.

title: fruit and nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine honey and orange juice in a small saucepan over medium heat and heat thoroughly. Add oil and vanilla. Stir with a whisk. Pour honey mixture over oat mixture and toss well. Spread out mixture onto a jelly-roll pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Bake an additional 10 minutes. Cool in pan. Place oat mixture back in the large bowl and stir in dried fruits. May be frozen.

title: blueberry dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: collard greens
directions: Open each leaf under running water in sink.
Clean both sides of the leaf.
Once done, roll the leaf up and slice the leaf in about 2-inch wide strips.

title: gourmet salad
directions: Chop fine the celery, carrot, radishes, onion and apple.
I prefer to use a Salad Shooter.
Cut tomato in small sections. Toss all ingredients together.
Top with nuts and cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Keeps well if thoroughly drained.
Serve with your favorite dressing.

title: bing cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Prepare pie crust for 8 inch pie (with lattice top).

title: dip the vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed until creamy.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the chicken with the vinegar and celery. In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, yogurt and tarragon.
Add this dressing to chicken mixture with salt and pepper to taste, mixing well.
The salad may be made a day in advance, kept covered and chilled.
Just before serving, stir in walnuts.

title: peggy's plantation dinner
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; drain.
Prepare noodles.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook all at low heat until all ingredients are warm and cheese is melted.

title: elbow macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and extract in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter.
Stir in chocolate syrup.
Spoon batters alternately into prepared bundt or tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer to make it light and fluffy.
Place in a 10 x 15-inch glass dish.

title: pan-fried potatoes
directions: Take frypan, add oil.
Slice onion, potatoes and cabbage.
Add water.
Cook 45 minutes, covered, on medium.
When almost done, add wieners, Polish sausage or any link meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Good main dish.

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown ground meat and onion soup mix.
Blend tomato sauce, water and rice. Shred cabbage in roaster.
Add meat, sauce and rice. Mix. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix occasionally.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Toss cooked macaroni with remaining ingredients.
Chill. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: shrimp cocktail appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese in glass pie plate; pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese and spread.
Then add layer of shrimp.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with a brush.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
In a large skillet, simmer potatoes, onion, peppers and garlic for 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, oregano, basil and pepper. Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes, until tender.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut sausage crosswise in small circles.
Put water, sausage and tomato paste in a boiler.
Let boil for about 10 minutes. Peel potatoes and cut in small pieces. Cut onion in small pieces.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Drain grease from sausage.
Combine all ingredients and stir until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Heat broth and add meal; stir about 10 minutes, until thickens. Mix bread crumbs, poultry seasoning, onion, celery and egg together.
Pour meal mixture over the bread crumb mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) at 350° or 375° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: cool whip pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham pie shells.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix butter in shallow casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over the melted butter, then pour sliced peaches.
Also add juice of peaches.
Add vanilla. Sprinkle on top 1 cup sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mounds balls
directions: Melt butter and stir in the other 3 ingredients.
When partly cool, shape in balls and chill until cold.
Melt chocolate chips and half bar of paraffin and dip balls.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into baking tins.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: no bake fruit and nut cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and shape as desired.
A lined cake tin or lined box.
Place some cherries on top and sides, if desired.
Put in refrigerator and chill 2 days before slicing.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; toss well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Put in a pan and pour chocolate chips over the top and melt.
Cool them and cut into squares.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Sift dry ingredients together. In mixing bowl, combine butter, flour mixture, 3/4 cup buttermilk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add chocolate, eggs and rest of buttermilk; beat well.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans, greased and floured.
Cool.
Spread filling between each layer. Serves 10.

title: black-eyed peas*
directions: First Day:

Cover about 2 pounds of ham shank (include skin and bone) and 1/4 to 1/2 pound smoked hog jowl with cold water in a 4-quart pot and boil gently for 2 hours or until the meat comes off the bone easily.
Chill overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place softened butter in a large mixer bowl.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add flour, eggs, buttermilk, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg lightly over top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Cool.
Decorate with sliced strawberries, blueberries or any fruit of your choice. Wonderful!

title: mexican vegetables
directions: In large skillet, saute the onions and garlic in the oil for 5 minutes.
Add the carrots; cover the pan and saute for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the remaining vegetables and seasonings and cook on low heat until the vegetables are just tender.
The mixture should be saucy; add more tomato juice, if necessary.
Serve over hot cornbread and top with sour cream or cheese.

title: low-fat cocoa squares
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs; stir in milk. Sift dry ingredients together, then stir into mixture.
Add nuts. Spread into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Frost while hot with Cocoa Frosting or Glaze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and onion.
Add egg gradually; beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot oil, where fish has been fried.
Fry until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for one hour or until done at 325°.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise, and onions.
Put into greased 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Sprinkle on crumbled bacon, olives, and Fritos in that order.
Bake 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shoo fly cake
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, sugar and shortening.
Take out 1/2 of mixture and set aside.
Mix molasses and warm water.
Make a well in crumb mixture and pour in molasses and water.
Add baking soda. Mix until blended.
Pour into ungreased pan.

title: stone ground wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup tepid water in a large mixing bowl; let stand about 10 minutes.
Scald milk, add shortening, sugar, butter
and salt and stir.	Add 1 cup room temperature water
and check for temperature between 110° and 140°.
Pour this
mixture into bowl with yeast and stir.
Add 3 cups bread flour and beat thoroughly.
Add 3 cups wheat flour a little at a
time and blend. Add wheat flour until dough consistency is reached
and
knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, cover
with a damp towel and rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; knead lightly 1 to 2 minutes.
Divide in two; shape into loaves	and
place
in greased 8 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until double
in bulk.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Place
on	a
cooling rack, baste with melted butter and cover with a damp towel for soft crust.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel eggs and dip in the beaten egg.
Then cover with sausage. Dip egg again in the beaten egg and then dip and roll into bread crumbs.
Fry about 10 minutes.
Serve plain or dip in mustard sauce.

title: census soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add potatoes and onions and mix well.
Add vegetables	together with liquid and add 2 to 3 cups of water. Add macaroni and simmer at least 45 minutes until potatoes and onions are done.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: easy gourmet chicken
directions: Butter a large roasting pan.
Sprinkle raw rice in pan, then add nuts and chicken.
Heat all liquids and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 275° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, undisturbed and uncovered.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir the flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and mix well.
Fold in dry ingredients and place in well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 10 x 12-inch cake pan or large skillet. Grease pan and bake at 450° until done.
I brown mine.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk.
Slowly add lime juice. Pour in crust.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top as you serve with whip cream.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: In mixing bowl beat eggs; blend with milk.
Combine sugar and tapioca.
Place bottom crust in pie plate, and add rhubarb. Cover with sugar and tapioca mixture.
Pour egg mixture over; dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry.
Cut slits in crust, to allow steam to escape.
If desired, brush crust with cream.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer, or until lightly browned.

title: green beans
directions: Bake until heated through and through.

title: oatmeal cake with topping
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In bowl, combine water, oatmeal and butter. Cover and let stand for 20 minutes. Add sugars, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and eggs. Mix well. Bake in 9 x 13 cake pan for at least 35 to 45 minutes.

title: whily's mac and cheese
directions: Cook Noodles and Drain.
Put in 9 X 13 glass dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 the Seasonings over noodles than put
1/2 the grated Cheese. Dot with butter, than 1/2 the Stewed Tomatoes.
Apply the next layer Seasonings, cheese, butter, tomatoes.
Mix
milk and juice from tomatoes and pour over top, dot with some more butter. Tin foil and bake 325 for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes to crisp top.

title: canadian schwartzies
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 - 10 people.
Freezes well.

title: green pea salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly in 6 mini meat loaves.
In skillet, brown loaves in shortening and drain off the fat.
Stir in remaining soup, seasoning and water.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with parsleyed potatoes and broccoli, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: souffle sandwich brementon
directions: Place 4 slices of bread in square cake pan, 9-inch.
On each, put slice of meat and slice of cheese and top with second slice of bread.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown stew meat; first, flour before browning.
Mix stew mix in pan.
After meat is cooked, add potatoes, carrots and peas; cook 1/2 hour.
You can use less potatoes, carrots and peas.

title: hamburger florentine soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 5-quart saucepan or Dutch oven.
Drain. Stir in all remaining ingredients, except spinach.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add frozen spinach.
Cover and simmer an additional 25 minutes.
Stir to blend spinach into soup.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 11 (1 1/3 cup) servings.

title: homemade granola(microwave)
directions: In a glass bowl mix sugar, honey, oil and cinnamon.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Add oats, coconut and nuts.
Toss to coat.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Mixture will become brown and crisp.
Stir in fruit.
Let mixture stand for 1 to 2 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times to break it up.
Mixture will become cool and crisp.
Store in tightly closed bottle or tin.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining five.
Mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: In a large bowl mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Add pineapple and bread cubes.
Pour into well greased casserole dish.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: lennie's chicken and dumplins
directions: Cook whole chicken in a large pot in plenty of water and seasonings.
(Can cook 6 chicken legs along with it for plenty of meat.)
Debone (keep chicken stock).
Cut Crisco into flour.
Add milk (like biscuit dough); work this up.
Roll out on floured surface thin and cut in strips.
Separate.
Have chicken stock boiling with lid on.

title: pita pizza wedges
directions: Split each pita round in half horizontally.
Quarter each round, forming 16 triangles total.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until crisp and golden. Spread pizza sauce over toasted triangles.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Return to oven and bake about 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring
margarine,
evaporated
milk and sugar to a boil over medium
heat,
stirring constantly.
Boil for 7 minutes. Remove from
heat
and add 1 cup crunchy peanut butter, 1 pint marshmallow
cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
