Stir until melted. Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, apple and celery; simmer.
Add water. Cook until chopped ingredients are tender and most of the liquid has cooked away.
Stir in seasonings; add cream and shrimp.
Cook gently, until cream is reduced to sauce consistency.
Serve over rice.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges peel side down in 2 shallow baking dishes.
Mix ingredients.
Brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and garlic and cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Add zucchini and cabbage; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and pepper.
Cook for an additional 1 minute.
Place about 2 tablespoons of beef mixture onto egg roll wrapper near a corner.
Fold over corner and then roll once.
Fold in sides and continue to roll, closing up beef mixture.
Beat one egg and coat edges of egg roll.
Press to seal.
Fry in 1 to 1 1/2-inches of hot salad oil.
Serve with Plum Sauce.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup to meat, mix well, and set aside.
Place tater tots in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cover with soup and meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 375 degrees until tater tots are fully cooked.

title: spinach bars
directions: Preparation Time: 10 to 15 minutes.
Cooking Time: 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes.
Pour oil in one hole, vinegar in the second hole and vanilla in the third hole.
Pour cold water over all and mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco pie with a spice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning.
In separate bowl mix sour cream and can of tomatoes.
In 9x13 inch pan layer Nachos, beef, black olives, sour cream and cheese.
Keep layering ending up wtih cheese on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine in order and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
the
oleo and Crisco;
add sugar and cream well. Add
1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, salt and nutmeg
mixture,
alternating
with milk.
Add flavoring. Sprinkle baking powder over batter.
Fold in.
Pour cake in a well-floured and
greased tube pan.
Put in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Start in a cold oven.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Make sure strawberries are thawed.
Add nuts and pour in glass dish.
Let set overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Crush until well broken up, but not a puree.
There should be 2 1/2 cups of crushed broccoli and cooking water. In large pot, heat butter, blend in flour and add milk, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Then add salt to taste, onion, cheese and crushed broccoli.
Reheat to boiling.
Serve and enjoy.

title: waffle surprise
directions: For Dutch Honey:
Cook white syrup, sugar, cream and vanilla until mixture thickens.
Pour over waffles.
Top with crushed pineapple, almond slivers and/or chocolate chips.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add remaining ingredients to bacon drippings. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon crumbs over top and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Grease cookie sheet and put frozen dough on and grease top and sides of bread dough.
Cover with waxed paper and let thaw.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot and heat.
Reduce heat to simmer and continue cooking about 1 hour.
Stir often.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot sauce to taste.

title: butterscotch apple dip
directions: Microwave:
In 1 quart glass bowl, combine milk, chips and salt.
Microwave on full power (High) 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve warm with apple wedges.
Can be served warm over ice cream.

title: zesty red potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes well; do not peel.
Place in large pot and cover with water.
Cook, covered, over medium-high heat about 30 minutes or until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, combine Ranch dressing mix, yogurt, mayonnaise and milk in a small bowl; set aside.
Remove cooked potatoes from heat; drain well.
While still warm, cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes and place in large bowl. Gently toss warm potatoes, celery, red pepper, green onion, parsley and yogurt dressing together until mixed well.
Garnish with paprika and chives and serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: master's men mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 8 x 8-inch container.
Layer sour cream on top of beans evenly, salsa on top of sour cream and cheese on top of salsa.
Sprinkle chives over cheese.
Ready to serve with tortilla chips.

title: angel hair and shrimp
directions: Prepare angel hair (capellini) according to directions on package.
Drain.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter (or margarine) on medium heat.
Add shrimp and garlic; cook and stir until shrimp are opaque, being careful not to burn garlic. Combine hot angel hair, shrimp mix, Parmesan cheese and pepper. Toss to mix.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2 to 4.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Good reheated.

title: energy bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine oats, cereal and sesame seed and toast over medium heat for a few minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, mix sugar, milk, egg and vanilla. Add melted chocolate and mix well.
Spread in a greased 8-inch pan.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rachel pafford's s'mores
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread peanut butter on saltines. Place marshmallows on top.
Place on cookie sheet and place in oven.
Remove and eat when marshmallows puff up and brown.

title: stir-fried sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken with scissors into 1 x 1 x 1/4-inch pieces.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add green onion, green pepper, celery and water chestnuts. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk. Add flour, melted butter, egg yolks and salt. Mix until smooth, then place in warm spot to rise for 2 to 3 hours. Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep hot fat. Fry until both sides are brown. Take them out and let cool a little, then place in bag with sugar and shake until doughnuts are covered.

title: artichoke-oyster soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add flour.
Blend in.
Add oyster liquid, chicken broth, artichokes and milk.
Season to taste.
I use Tony's.
Simmer (do not boil) for 10 minutes.
Add oysters, chopped green onions and parsley before serving.
Simmer 5 minutes.
If too thick, add a little hot water or thicken with a little cornstarch and water.

title: "quakers"(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats, then add dry ingredients. Beat well.
Put 1/4 cup sugar in small bowl.
Dip fingers into sugar; pinch off a bit of dough and roll into size and shape of walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen large thick cookies.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix in order given.
May store uncooked batter in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Spoon into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Tops should be light golden brown.

title: banana chocolate chip nut bread
directions: Mash bananas well with mixer.
Add all other ingredients (except nuts and chips) and mix well.
Add nuts and chips and mix by hand, folding into batter.
Pour into two greased (use butter or oil) 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes and test or 4 or 5 small pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then with sausage.
Mix together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover tightly with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° (or until eggs are set).

title: easy scalloped corn
directions: Melt margarine in large microwave-safe bowl.
Add corn; mix well.
Mix in eggs, sour cream, sugar and corn bread mix; stir well.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir sugar and milk over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage, 234°.
Remove quickly and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Blend.

title: dream salad
directions: Fix Dream Whip as directed on pkg. Combine softened cream cheese with Dream Whip on medium mixer speed. Mix jello with 1 c. boiling water. Put cherries, bananas, and pineapple into jello. Mix with Dream Whip mixture. Chill until jelled.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Add soda to milk.
Let stand for at least 5 minutes.
To this, add sugar and syrup.
Cook until it reaches the soft ball stage. Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts. Beat until it begins to thicken and loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Pour into buttered pan or dish.
Cut with set.

title: turkey gumbo soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Rinse and place in 6 qt. pot.
Peel and slice carrots. Slice celery.
Rinse both and add to potatoes. Quarter and slice onion and stir into other vegetables.
Heat and simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and enough water to cover.
Simmer 1 hours and serve.
Soup will be thick and hearty.
For thinner soup, add water or broth.

title: granny's russian tea
directions: Boil spices in 1-quart water for 5 minutes.
Strain; add sugar, Karo syrup, tea and juices.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine oats and baking soda; add to butter mixing, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: seafood quiche
directions: *Can use
6 1/2-ounce can crab and 4 1/2-ounces shrimp for example.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Boil sugar, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda. Stir.
Add to popped corn and place on cookie sheets.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool. Store in covered container to keep
crisp.

title: pimiento and cheese spread
directions: Combine the cheese and pimiento and mix well.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
This will make enough spread for 10 regular size sandwiches.
I usually cut the edges off the bread slices before adding the spread.
Each sandwich is then cut into
4 portions making 40 tea sandwiches.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown meat, add celery, onion, and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from burner.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 30-35 minutes until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep refrigerated.
Excellent for a fresh relish tray.

title: pumpkin crunch pudding cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs, cinnamon and allspice or nutmeg.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with wax paper.
Pour dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Spoon butter over nuts evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Invert on serving platter and cover with frosting.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour into bowl and chill until ready to serve. Sets in about 2 hours. Best if sets overnight.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into skillet.
Pour milk into skillet and mix.
Cook until thickened.
If thinner consistency desired, add more milk.

title: mom's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water until tender.
Cool and cut in bite-size pieces.
Place chicken in large bowl.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1/2 soup can of chicken broth saved from the boiled chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour and mix together.
Put bottom crust in 10-inch pie pan and fill with chicken mixture. Cover with top pie crust and cut about 6 (1/2-inch) slits in the crust.
Cook at 400° for about 40 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Cut
squash
in
rings;
peel and remove seeds.
Cut in small pieces.
Cook in small amount of water;
drain and mash. Beat
egg yolks in a little milk.
Add margarine, egg, all the flavorings and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into squash.
Pour into
a
quart greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: minted pineapple and smoky links
directions: Drain 1 can pineapple.
Heat pineapple chunks and juice and chunks from the second can with mint leaves or extract to taste. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, brown smoky links and mix with pineapple, which has been heated through and drained.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and cream well.
Then add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut into desired shape. Bake until browned.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Bake rolls
at	time
and temperature on package after rolling them out flat on cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: tom's terrific tomato sauce
directions: Grate onion and carrot and then saute them in olive oil over medium heat for about 4 minutes.
Add crushed garlic and continue to cook for another minute.
Then add the tomatoes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain juice from peaches and
add
water to make 3 to 4 cups. Add sugar and bring
to
a	boil.
Mix dry ingredients, cut
in shortening.
Add
milk.
Roll
in
rectangles.
Spread with peaches.
Roll up like
jelly roll and slice 1 1/2-inches thick. Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour boiling syrup over this and bake at 325°
for
minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg over top.
Can use apples.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Drain and mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: torte-a-lets
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until light.
Place vanilla wafer in cupcake papers.
Fill 3/4 full of cheese and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 24.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Separate eggs and add egg yolks to mixture.
Add flour.
Fold in beaten egg white and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan for 25 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: sugar cookie hearts
directions: Chill 1 hour.
Roll and cut 1/4-inch thick.
Cut heart shape and bake on ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with red sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until edges start to brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: diatetic cake
directions: Soften
margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: move over mr. reese bars
directions: Place broken graham crackers in food processor and process to crumb stage (medium fine).
Add powdered sugar and mix.
Then add peanut butter and melted butter. Process until mixed well; dough will be firm.

title: beef chunks in sour cream
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour; brown in shortening.
Add onion and brown.
Add mushrooms, water and spices.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 3/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally. While cooking stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake mix of your choice in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to the directions of the cake mix.
Cool.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip, a layer of sliced bananas, layer of Cool Whip, layer of pie filling and a layer of Cool Whip.
Dribble with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: tex mex cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add vegetable oil and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Blend in shredded carrots and crushed pineapple.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
(Note:
Can line pans with wax paper.) Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cucumbers and sour cream dressing
directions: Pare and slice the cucumbers; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Let stand for 30 minutes, then press out any excess water between pieces of paper towels.
Combine remaining ingredients and gently mix with the cucumbers.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Add cherries (or peaches sprinkled with cinnamon) and 1/2 cup water.
Sprinkle on 1 cup sugar.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and jello.
Add egg and vanilla. Gradually add flour and baking powder.
Roll in balls and press with fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Combine butter, Crisco, eggs, milk, vanilla, almond and salt. Mix well.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Pour this into butter and Crisco mixture and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Place in cold oven and set at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs and mix well, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Use deep-dish pie shell.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Roll out on floured towel (not terry).
Knead with towel.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 30 minutes before cooking.

title: spinach and feta cheese quiche
directions: Drain the spinach and squeeze out as much moisture as possible, it should be fairly dry.
Mix the eggs, cream and milk.
Add the salt, pepper, lemon juice and parsley.
Stir in spinach and Feta cheese.
Fill the quiche crust, and place the Parmesan or Romano cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center comes out dry.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into large chunks.
In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook ground chuck, onions and seasonings until done.
Cook spaghetti, drain.
Put spaghetti in casserole with meat mixture on top.
Dilute soup and pour over casserole.
Top with cheese. Cover, bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together; put in casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan, turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown or tests done.
Filling will sink into cake while baking.
Place bottom side down on serving plate, dust with powdered sugar.
Spoon lightly sweetened whipped cream over top. This is great warm.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: brie with lentils
directions: In a small skillet, saute onion until it is transparent.
Drain soup and add lentils to onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: spicy bistro steak subs
directions: Melt margarine in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic and next 6 ingredients (roast beef through beer) and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Place drained roast beef on buttered and toasted hoagie buns. Serve sandwiches with reserved sauce for dipping.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat butter over double boiler until melted.
Stir in beaten egg yolk, cream, grated cheese and salt.
Heat, stirring with whisk occasionally, until smooth.
Drain noodles; toss with cream mixture until evenly coated.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and pepper.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the bottle of Pepsi, bottle of barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir together on stove top on medium heat.
Roll chicken in flour and add to saucepan.
Cook until done.
Really good!

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In a small bowl, lightly beat egg whites and set aside.
In al large bowl, vomine 2/3 cup of coocoa and cornstarch.
Whisk 3/4 cup of milk into cocoa mixture until completely smooth.

title: mum's johnny bull pudding
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add egg and molasses.
Add sour milk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add allspice, cinnamon, raisins, nuts and salt.
Mix all together.
Add flour to batter consistency (not too stiff).
Pour into cloth and tie top or into pan (our mum used part of daddy's lunch bucket).
Place in steamer and steam for 3 hours.

title: muffin pan rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients at one time.
Mix well.
Put into muffin pans and bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour and pepper.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Quarter and fry corn tortillas lightly.
Set aside.
In a skillet, fry beef, garlic and onion until brown.
Combine soup, tomatoes, chili powder and chilies (drained and diced); salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with meat mixture.
Layer on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan:
sauce, tortillas and grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco ribs
directions: Place ribs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Roast in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine the taco seasoning mix with the water, sherry and catsup; pour over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with pan juices.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Cut turkey into thin strips or cubes; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet on medium-high.
Add garlic, carrots, onion and mushrooms; cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: main dish potato salad
directions: Cook peeled potatoes.
Cool and dice.
Mix in celery.
Cook veal; cool and dice.
Grind onion and diced pimiento.
Add with veal to potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste, then mix with salad dressing and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Combine 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until set.

title: low-fat french toast
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Blend.
Heat Teflon griddle over medium-high heat.
Dip bread one slice at a time into egg mixture, coating both sides evenly.
Brown 2 to 3 minutes, turn and brown 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Use ice or ice ring.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
eggs and beat well.
Melt white chocolate over hot	water,	then
add
to first mixture. Sift flour, baking powder,
soda
and salt.
Then add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour
into greased and floured cake pans. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place ground beef in center of roasting pan.
Cut up potatoes, carrots and onion and place around meat.
Sprinkle soup mix over the meat and vegetables.
Add 2 cups water, or enough to cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, cheese, salt, pepper and cream.
Melt margarine and add bread crumbs.
Combine bread crumbs and squash mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook chicken and onion in broth.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer until potatoes and onions are done.
Meanwhile, brown 1 pound of ground meat in skillet.
Drain meat.
Add to soup and let simmer until all of the flavors have blended.

title: my grandma's hummingbird cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook until it thickens into a soft ball.
Allow it to cool enough to handle. Knead the dough.
While kneading, add a drop or 2 of oil of clove, oil of spearmint or peppermint extract.
Store in an airtight container.

title: val's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, nonfat dry milk, raisins, honey and coconut.
Form into balls.
Roll in sesame seeds or coconut.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well the mashed bananas and eggs together in a bowl.
Sift flour, sugar and baking soda together.
Add to banana mixture. Stir well.
Put in a buttered loaf pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: festive pineapple boat
directions: Stand pineapple up and cut about a third off one side, leaving the top attached.
Remove fruit from the piece cut off and discard outer peel.
Remove fruit from the remaining pineapple, leaving a 1/2 in. shell intact.
Cut pineapple into bite- size pieces; toss with bananas and kiwi.
Spoon into "Boat".
Combine brown sugar, pecans, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over fruit. Sprinkle with coconut.
Garnish with strawberries if desired. Serve immediately.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup of butter in 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and stir until blended.
Drain pineapple well; reserve 2 tablespoons of syrup.
Arrange pineapple in butter-sugar mixture.
Place cherry in center of each pineapple.
Beat remaining 1/3 cup of butter with 1/2 cup of sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, lemon peel, juice and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and 2 tablespoons of pineapple juice. Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add 1/4 cup of sugar to make stiff meringue.
Fold into batter.
Pour over pineapple in skillet.
Bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes until cake tests done.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm or cold.

title: beef roast
directions: Cut slits through meat; insert slivers of garlic and onions into slits.
Pour vinegar into slits.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Pour off vinegar.
Place in heavy pot and brown in oil. Pour black coffee and water over roast.
Cook slowly for 6 hours. Season with salt 20 minutes before end of cooking time.

title: creme doodles
directions: Stir together above ingredients.
Shape by teaspoon into 1 inch balls and chill.

title: butter brickle dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and butter brickle together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt fat and add garlic or onion.
When onion is slightly browned, add ground meat.
Add flour, salt and chili powder to meat and blend together.
Then add canned tomatoes and hot water.
Add kidney beans.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or put in crock-pot and cook on low for a few hours.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Beat together eggs, sugar, syrup and chocolate mixture.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: low-fat honey mustard dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and whisk or blend together. Great on salads or sandwiches.
Will keep in refrigerator about 1 week.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Contains per 1/4 cup: fat 0.25 g; cholesterol 0 g; calories 40.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Bring
enough
water
to cover shrimp to a boil in large pot. Add
shrimp (in shell) to boiling water.
Bring to boil a second time and boil approximately 5 minutes until shrimp turns pink. Drain.
Shell
and	remove	vein.
To melted butter, add garlic, parsley,
paprika,	cayenne
and
cooking sherry.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs; toss lightly.
Place shrimp in 11 x 7 x
1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon the butter and crumb mixture over shrimp. Bake
at
for
minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: red hot punch
directions: Heat over low heat until red hots melt.
Add water.
Serve hot.
Wonderful hot drink when you have a sore throat.

title: winter vegetables
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. saucepan over medium heat, melt butter until hot.
Cook onion with thyme until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.

title: barbecued chopped ham
directions: Cook all ingredients, except ham, for 45 minutes.
Add the ham.
Heat in oven for 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple baked ham slice
directions: Place ham slice in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Allow 1/3 to 1/2 pound of meat per serving.
Insert whole clove into ham at 1-inch intervals.
Sprinkle over ham, a mixture of brown sugar, bread crumbs, lemon peel and dry mustard.

title: burghul pilaf
directions: Melt Crisco in a heavy skillet; then add dry burghul.
Braise well.
Fry onion in separate pan until golden.
Mix with burghul; add broth and seasonings.
Stir well and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir well and bake again for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: diabetic caramel popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn evenly in large, shallow baking pan.
In small saucepan, melt margarine and blend in honey.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat all pieces.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool slightly in pan before removing.
May be stored in an airtight container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, oatmeal, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, tomato paste, tomato sauce and egg.
Mix well and mound into a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, mustard, worcestershire sauce and water in a shaker; pour over meat.
Ketchup may be poured over the top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef steak soup
directions: Melt oleo in pot.
Cut steak into pieces; roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Place meat into pot and brown until soft.
Add mixed vegetables, water and tomatoes.

title: chicken in coconut "milk" curry
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat. Mix in garlic paste, ginger paste, cayenne pepper and turmeric. Add chicken and cook in mixture for 15 to 20 minutes with frequent stirring.
Add chicken broth; cover the pot and cook for another 15 minutes on medium setting, stirring occasionally.
Add coconut milk and stir it in.
Mix split pea flour in 1/3 cup chicken broth (it will be lumpy, but you should be patient and stir it to remove the lumps); add to the pot and mix in thoroughly.
Bring the pot to boil; reduce heat to medium-low and replace lid.
Cook for another 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add salt to taste; if you like it a little tangy, you can add some citric acid to taste. You can eat this curry over rice or spaghetti.
Enjoy!

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Chop onions (tops and all) and green pepper.
Mince garlic. In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add chunked chicken.
Sprinkle in spices.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add all vegetables.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add Ro-Tel and broth and stir in rice (not Minute rice); bring to a boil.
Stir and cover.
Reduce to low heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and let it melt.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add green onions, parsley and shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes. Slowly add flour and half and half cream, then add cheese and melt.
Add salt, garlic and pepper and cook 20 minutes.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix everything together in large baking dish. Bake until it bubbles (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: tuna cheese pie
directions: Pierce pastry shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes; set aside.
In a large bowl, toss together next 3 ingredients.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise and milk.
Add to first ingredients and mix.
Pour into shell.
Put 3-inch strips of aluminum foil around edge of pie dish, then take it off 10 minutes before its done, so edge won't burn.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven or until done.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cook pintos as usual.
When almost done, brown meat and onion and add to beans.
Stir.
Add diced potatoes.
Cook on simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with cornbread (we used hot water cornbread).

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill for several hours.
Serve with fish or any seafood.

title: breakfast omelet
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Layer shredded frozen hash browns.
Next, layer of cheese.
Next, 1 pound ham (sausage) and onion.
Options:
mushrooms, green onions, green pepper.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Boil potatoes until soft and mash until real soft.
Add shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Beat eggs until light, then add 1 cup sugar,
baking powder, nutmeg and salt to taste.
Mix well and add enough flour to roll out and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in deep
fat
at 365° until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper and sprinkle or roll in powdered sugar.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, salt and water.
Bring to a boil; boil only 2 minutes.
Put marshmallow cream in large bowl.
Pour hot syrup in bowl all at once and beat until it loses its glossy look.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves together.
Beat sugar, shortening and eggs in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Add and beat in the pumpkin.
Add flour mixture in 3 additions alternating with milk and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and dates/raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix.
Stir mayonnaise and sour cream until blended.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
You may add onions if you want to.
Chill; stir before serving.

title: hot rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix in flour (you might need to add a little more flour).
Knead dough.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise 1 hour.
Make rolls; let rise again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili beef stew
directions: Dust beef with flour; brown well on all sides in hot shortening.
Stir in soup, water and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, potatoes and green pepper.
Cover and cook one hour longer or until beef and vegetables are tender; stir occasionally.
Add onions and continue cooking for 5 minutes.
This recipe makes 4 servings.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and pie filling, mixing well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Mix other ingredients together and stir mixture into slightly cooled bacon grease, then pour over lettuce. Crumble bacon over top.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle with water, mixing lightly until dough just holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Roll on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into rounds 5 to 6-inches in diameter. Spoon 2 tablespoons fruit into half of each round.
Fold in half. Press edges together with fork to seal.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or fry in deep hot fat (360°) until brown.
Yields 8 to 10 pies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together; put in lightly greased cake pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine; pour over corn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and noodles.
Place in well buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Cover with noodles.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: do-it-yourself croutons
directions: Lightly spread margarine on both sides of bread. Sprinkle with garlic and/or other spices. Dice and place on cookie sheet. Toast for 1 hour or until crisp, stirring occasionally.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup canned milk and butter. Pour 1/2 of batter into 13 x 9 x 2 greased and floured pan and bake for 5 minutes at 350°. It will be gooey and puffy.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook until firm, about 1 hour.

title: cry babies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; combine with coconut, walnuts and raisins.
Add all dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 9 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in a 13 x 9-inch dish for 1 hour at 400°.

title: all-american pot roast
directions: Heat oil over medium heat in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add beef and brown on all sides.
Add next 8 ingredients; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and simmer 30 to 45 more minutes until carrots are tender and beef reaches desired doneness.
Stir water and cornstarch together until smooth.
Remove beef from pot and stir cornstarch into juices.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat to make gravy.
Add mushrooms to gravy, if desired.

title: boerenmeisjes cocktail
directions: This cocktail being sweeter than the Boerenjongens cocktail, is often served to the Dutch women while the men drink Boerenjongens.

title: cornish hen and rice bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Using kitchen shears or sharp knife, cut hens in half lengthwise through breast-bone.
In 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish, combine rice mix, onion, celery and mushrooms.
Heat water and dissolve bouillon; stir into rice mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Place game hens cut side down over rice.
Brush with 1 tablespoon honey; lightly sprinkle with salt.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; brush hens with remaining honey.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes longer or until tender and brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put cup of water on stove until butter melts.
Add salt and flour and beat fast.
Cool.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes and at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: aunt ruth's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in 1/4 cup water.
Cool.
Cream sugar and lard. Add eggs and mix.
Mix soda with 1 tablespoon water and add to mixture.
Add salt, nutmeg, flour and oatmeal; mix.
Fold in raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 375°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix eggs and condensed milk.
Slowly add lime juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let ingredients stand until room temperature.
Chop into chunks.
Mix in mixer until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator until completely chilled.
Form into 2 large or 3 small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain any excess grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: baked bean salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Brown in bacon fat onion and green pepper. Combine tomato paste, sugar, vinegar and Tabasco sauce to taste. Pour over onion and pepper and heat.
Combine baked beans, kidney beans, green beans and butter beans.
Add beans to pepper and onion sauce; mix.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Add first 9 ingredients together.
Simmer sauce while cooking chicken.
Dip breast fillets in beaten egg, then in flour or bread crumbs.
Saute in oil until brown.

title: butternut coconut cake
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add milk and flour, beating well.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour batter into three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Frost with Seven Minute Icing.
Spread crushed pineapple between layers along with icing and coconut.
Cover top and sides with icing and top with fresh coconut.

title: party chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and paprika. Grill on each side until done (do not overcook).
Place in a baking dish or skillet.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix and pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: marie's chocolate fudge(this is expensive, but it makes a lot!)
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugar in a large heavy saucepan. Place over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil.

Cover and boil exactly 5 minutes. Turn heat to very low. Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved. Add chocolate, sweet chocolate and chocolate bits, one at a time, stirring after each addition until completely melted. Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into lightly buttered oblong pan (such as an 18 x 12-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides).
Let stand until firm before cutting into squares.
Be sure the fudge is completely cooled before sealing in container.
Makes about 125 (1-inch) squares.

title: meat ball seasoned rice
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, water (1/4 cup) and salts.
Shape into balls.
Brown in hot oil in skillet.
Push to one side; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in soup mixture, rice and 2 1/2 cups water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until rice is fluffy.

title: amaretto freezes
directions: Combine in blender and blend until smooth.
Can use chocolate ice cream and delete the creme de cacao.

title: percolator punch 1
directions: Pour all juices in a large percolator.
Place all spices and sugar into the basket.
Perk and serve hot.

title: stir-fry ramen salad
directions: Combine cabbage and green onions.
Cover and store in fridge until ready to serve.
In frypan, melt margarine and add noodles, sesame seed and almonds, stirring until browned.
Drain and cool on paper towel.
Sprinkle over cabbage and onions.

title: cube steaks(with mushrooms and onions)
directions: Flour, salt and pepper both sides of cube steaks.
Use roaster pan with lid.
Spray roaster with Pam.
Put in cube steaks.
Cook 30 minutes at 325 or 350 degrees.
After 30 minutes turn steaks and add mushrooms and onions.
Cook for another 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry dessert salad
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients in a quart jar. Shake well. Keep in cupboard. When ready to use, mix 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of HOT water.

title: mom's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix with
fork.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk.
Mix into a ball.
Knead good. Dough should be soft.
Make out biscuits.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: three-way bean salad
directions: Mix the sugar, vinegar, hot water, salt and salad oil, then add the beans, celery and onions.
Chill.

title: fluffer nutter
directions: Equipment Needed:
1 sandwich knife, 1 sandwich plate and 1 (10 ounce) drinking glass.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly until thick.
Add raisins, lemon juice and butter.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake in buttered dish at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with round pumpernickel bread.
Note:
To wash vegetables well, place in large pan and cover with cold water; let stand.
Sand will settle to the bottom.
Shake vegetables while still in the water to release sand still in vegetables.
Lift out, put on towels and pat dry with paper towels.
Let stand to air dry a little.

title: summer spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in large bowl; add tomatoes, zucchini, cucumbers and peppers. Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over the salad and toss to coat.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Can make the night before.
Makes A LOT!!

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly; drain fat.
Remove crust from bread.
Cut in quarters.
Layer bread, cheese, sausage, bread, etc.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over all.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Use a 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream the margarine and 1/4 cup of sugar.
Add flour and pecans; mix well.
Shape into 1-tablespoon balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mountains
directions: Cream the shortening and sifted sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with the milk to cream mixture. Add melted chocolate and additional melted fat. Add chopped nuts last.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Top with candied cherries and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 126 cookies 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: pancakes
directions: Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Mix remaining dry ingredients together.
Lightly beat the egg together with the oil and add to the buttermilk/soda mixture.
Pour liquid ingredients, as mixed, into dry ingredients and combine lightly.
This should be a thin batter, to make tender, thin pancakes.
Cook on a hot griddle, taking care to keep pancakes no more than three inches in diameter.

title: angel delite
directions: Put cake in 10 x 6-inch oblong Pyrex dish.
Put bananas and strawberries over cake.
Prepare gelatin.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin thickens slightly. Remove remaining ice.
Gently whip Cool Whip into gelatin mixture. Pour over cake and fruit.
Refrigerate approximately 1 hour.
Top with extra Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and let stand until cool.
Then pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt morsels over low heat; stir in other ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper to harden.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, eggs, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Best served while warm.

title: ramps and eggs
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Cook ramps in bacon grease until tender.
Beat eggs and add to ramps.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook eggs to desired degree of doneness (soft, medium or hard).
This dish is best cooked in an old iron frying pan.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Put ingredients in bowl or blender and mix very well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. This makes its own crust!

title: strawberry cream dessert
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour, oleo and nutmeats.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.
A quick dessert for unexpected company.

title: beef and vegetable pizza(cooking light)
directions: Cook meat, onion and minced garlic in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Return meat mixture to skillet; add tomato paste and next 5 ingredients, stirring well. Cook over medium-low heat 4 minutes or until cheese melts. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Add salt and sugar gradually, stirring well after each addition (mixture will be very grainy).
Then add milk gradually, mixing well after each addition, after last addition, cook for 5 to 6 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir.
Put into pint size jar.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and pie filling.
Add oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce lined plates, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.
Works well as a salad or dessert.

title: chicken and fried rice
directions: Let chicken set in soy sauce overnight. Fry chicken in a little oil. Cook rice and drain off water. Fry rice, mushrooms, bamboo sprouts, water chestnuts and green onions.
Mix in chicken and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts into a bowl.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over them and add beaten eggs.
Mix well by hand and bake in slow oven at 260° to 300° for 1 3/4 hours.
Place pan with 2 cups water on bottom shelf while baking.

title: summer zucchini casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt, baking powder and flour together.
Stir in parsley, onion, garlic and chiles.
Pour over zucchini and mix.
Add cheese and mix.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix croutons and butter; arrange on top of zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes before testing to see if done.
Cover loosely to prevent croutons from burning, or croutons may be added during the last few minutes of baking.
Serves 12.

title: jello
directions: Heat strawberry jello; put 1/2 cup water and heat it up to 500°.
Put it in a big pan and put it in the frigerator.
Leave it there until dinner.

title: meringue that won't weep
directions: Mix the cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water and cook over low heat until mixture is clear.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, whip egg whites until peaked, then slowly add cornstarch/sugar/water mixture and beat until creamy.
Add salt and the rest of the sugar and beat again until fluffy.
Pile on the pie and bake in a 350° oven until meringue is gold-tinged (usually 20 to 30 minutes).

title: mushroom soup
directions: Put beef broth in a soup pot.
Add celery, onion and carrots. Bring to a boil and simmer until tender.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Return to stock pot and simmer.
Saute mushrooms in lemon juice until tender.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and sherry to simmering broth.
Heat.
Place a slice of toasted French bread in individual soup bowls and ladle soup over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley, if desired.

title: swiss cheese puffs
directions: Combine water, margarine and salt in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add the flour all at once and stir the mixture over heat until mixture forms a ball (follows spoon around pan).
Cool slightly and blend in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well until mixture is smooth and well mixed, then blend in 1 cup of Swiss cheese.

title: light-n-crisp belgian waffles
directions: Preheat waffle maker.
Put all ingredients except egg whites in large bowl.
Beat on low until moistened.
Increase to medium, mix until smooth.
By hand gently fold in beaten eggs whites. Pour 1/2 cup batter over center of grids.
Bake until golden about 2 - 2 1/2 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: scalloped zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini covered in salt water until tender.
Drain chopped zucchini.
Cook sausage and onion until brown.
Drain off fat.
Reserve 2 tablespoons cheese.
Add remaining cheese, squash and liquid, crackers, eggs, salt and thyme to sausage.
Mix well. Turn in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° until set, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in pineapple juice.
Add eggs.
Cook over moderate heat.
Stir until thick and add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Bring water and remaining salt and oil to boil in a large pot.
Add pasta.
Cook to package directions.
Rinse with water and drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine juice and pasta.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in sealed container.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan or use bacon grease to saute onion. Add meat, steak sauce, salt, pepper and peppers.
When meat is cooked, add raw rice.
Simmer until rice begins to fry.
Drain liquid from peas.
Add water to get 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Add liquid; cover and cook 40 minutes (until rice is tender).
Add peas and mix well.
Simmer another 20 minutes.

title: barbecued spare ribs(fast barbecued spare ribs)
directions: Boil ribs until tender, place in 9 x 13 pan.
Add sauce above and bake at 350° until tender.

title: chili seasonings
directions: Blend all ingredients on high until fine.
Stop blender 2 to 3 times to stir.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Chill in fridge. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken liver salad with walnut vinaigrette(makes 8 servings)
directions: Whisk vinegar and lemon juice in small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add liver and saute just until cooked through, approximately 6 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss greens and arugula in bowl with enough vinaigrette to season.
Top with warm chicken livers.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in round pizza pan in order given.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: raisin pie supreme
directions: Combine juices, water, honey, salt and rind.
Heat to boiling. Moisten cornstarch in a little cold water and add to hot mixture. Rinse raisins and stir into hot mixture.
Line a deep pan with pastry; sprinkle flour on bottom.
Cover with top crust and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pie should be nearly cool when cut.
If it is allowed to cool, it should be heated slightly before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: juicy venison
directions: Put meat in crock-pot or cooking bag.
Dump salsa on top. Cook on high 4 hours in crock-pot or 2 hours in oven at 325°. Salt and pepper to taste after cooking (salt will make venison tough if added prior to cooking).

title: my own beef stroganoff
directions: Beat steak with cola bottle top on both sides.
Cut steak in thin strips; dredge in seasoned flour.
Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in 1/2 cup butter about 4 minutes.
Add remaining butter and meat, cook for about 3 more minutes (stirring continuously). Remove from heat and remove steak and vegetables.
Pour all but about 6 tablespoons of drippings in cup.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour and mix with drippings left in pan.
Add consomme.
Stir until thick but smooth.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir and cook on medium-low heat until well blended.
Add meat and vegetables and serve over rice, egg noodles or toast.

title: squash casserole
directions: Blanche yellow squash and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except for cheese and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sauce; mix well and let congeal.

title: petticoat tails
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, sugar and flavoring.
Sift together and stir in the flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Press and mold into smooth roll about 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until stiff.
(Several hours or overnight.)
With thin, sharp knife, cut into thin slices, 1/8-inch thick.
Place slices a little apart on ungreased baking pan.
Bake until slightly browned at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen. This cookie can be iced when cooled.

title: quick chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Brush chicken with sauce before broiling. Makes 1 cup.

title: coconut salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cut mango, onion and tomatoes; add to already made Italian dip for veggies.
Shake Parmesan cheese in it; add cooked, drained spaghetti and mix together.
Cool and serve.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, then hot water.
Add sifted flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on slightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned on bottom.
Turn stove on broil and let top brown.
Watch cookies closely so not to burn.
You may use raisins instead of chocolate chips; add 1 teaspoon cinnamon with raisins.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, except for bread.
Fold in bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut oatmeal chewies
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and peanut butter.
Add oats and flour.
Mix well. Spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done. Cool and cut into bars.

title: lemon broccoli salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cut broccoli into small cubes.
Add broccoli and onion; stir until broccoli thaws and separates.
Mix cottage cheese, mayonnaise and mustard. Add to gelatin.
Pour into individual dishes or a bowl.
Chill until set.
You could use sugar-free jello.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend vanilla and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with shaved chocolate before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except 1/2 can of tomato sauce. Put in pan sprayed with Pam.
Put remaining tomato sauce and additional picante sauce on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake for one hour.
Remove foil and bake another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges. Boil cloves and cinnamon in 1 quart of water for 5 minutes. Strain juice. Add boiled mixture, sugar and tea. Serve hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill 8 x 14-inch pan with apples.
Add honey, coriander and salt.
Cover with topping and bake approximately 40 minutes in a 375° oven until apples are tender.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash wild rice and drain.
Put in 3 cups boiling water and let stand 15 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile, brown meat and onion in butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients and rice.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours in 3-quart casserole.

title: italian sausage zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Place sausage in large pot.
Add onion, tomatoes and all seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add zucchini, celery, pepper and water.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese when you serve.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce
directions: Marinate chicken in lemon juice and pepper for 30 minutes. Cook chicken breasts in hot butter or margarine over medium heat for 8 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through; turn occasionally.
Remove chicken from pan and place on a warm platter; cover to keep warm.
Reserve drippings in pan.
Add the mushrooms and chives to the pan and drippings.
Cook and stir until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in the whipping cream; boil gently until slightly thickened, scraping the browned bits from the pan.
Spoon the sauce over warm chicken breasts and serve. Serves 4.

title: jim's casserole
directions: Combine.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream filling for cakes
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten egg. Add milk and cook over boiling water until thick.
Cool and add vanilla.

title: corn casserole
directions: Crumble cooked bacon.
Mix and cook the corn, peppers and onion about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bacon.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese sauce
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli.
Put in pan with 3/4 of broccoli covered in water.
Add 1 teaspoon of margarine.
Boil approximately five minutes, until tender.
Make sure it doesn't lose its color.

title: nacho dip
directions: Place refried beans in 12-inch glass pan; spread evenly, then spread sour cream over beans.
Spread salsa over sour cream.
Add black olives, cheese and tomatoes.
Dip nachos as desired.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; cut cheese in small cubes and mix cheese, sour cream and seasonings lightly through the beans.
Place in ungreased 2 quart dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cook until when dropped in cold water, it breaks like ice.
Add soda and stir rapidly.
Pour out in pan sprayed with Pam.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: applesauce, cranberry, cherry mold(salad)
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberry sauce and water, stirring occasionally.
Cook over medium heat until cranberry sauce is melted.
Pour over gelatin in large bowl.
Stir with wire whisk until dissolved.
Stir in mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in cranberry juice and lemon juice.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease baking dish.
Combine baking mix and water; stir until dough forms.
Press dough into bottom and up sides, using fingertips (dip fingers into baking mix so they won't stick to mixture).

title: chocolate-dipped crispy pops
directions: Mix cereal, melted margarine and marshmallows together.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir 1 of the containers of candy sprinkles. Press mixture into spray-coated pan.
Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: chicken 'n noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cornflakes and butter. Add a couple of drops of yellow food color to give the dish a yellow color (not cream).
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle the cornflakes on the top; dot with butter.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and serve cold.
Will keep for up to a week in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In an oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Remove dish from oven.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken.
Bake 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain fat off beef.
Drain water off cooked macaroni.
Mix ingredients together.
Add tomato soup.
Stir well.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: lo-cal oven fries
directions: Place quartered potatoes lengthwise on nonstick bakery pan. Add the oil; sprinkle with garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 20 minutes at 450°, or until done.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Brush over steaks.
Broil 3 minutes on each side or until done.

title: fruit and yogurt shake
directions: In a blender container, combine undrained peaches, banana, yogurt and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes; cover and blend until frothy. Makes 2 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Make in small balls.
Cook on top of stove in some Wesson oil until brown, drain off fat.
You can freeze until you want them.
(Bake or cook on top of stove 30 to 40 minutes.)

title: three bean casserole
directions: Drain lima and kidney beans.
Mix with pork and beans.
Brown bacon, hamburger and onion together.
Drain well.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and salt.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Before the last 10 minutes add the French fried onion rings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, pepper sauce and mashed beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spoon a little bean mixture over bottom of 6-cup round casserole.
Alternately layer tortillas and bean mixture, ending with tortillas.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into wedge-shaped portion to serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar; beat until thick and creamy.
Add margarine and milk.
Mix. Sift 3 cups of flour with baking powder and salt; add to batter.
Add just enough flour to make a dough that can be rolled.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut out doughnuts with doughnut cutter.
Heat oil to 375°.
Gently lift doughnuts into it a couple at a time.
Fry doughnuts, turning twice, until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
While doughnuts are still warm, shake in a paper bag with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Pour the boiling water over the saltines. Add all ingredients. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Follow directions to cake mix.
Let cake cool.
With a spaghetti fork utensil, poke holes into cake.
Make holes big enough to pour jello into them.
Follow directions to jello mix; put jello in refrigerator just a few minutes to cool down.
Pour jello over cake and into holes.
Let set about 15 minutes.
Spread Reddi Whip over cake like you would icing.
Rinse fresh strawberries and cut into 1/2 depending on size.
Place on top of Reddi Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook at 350° until thickens (about 1 hour). When butter melts, stir into mixture.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil. Remove from stove and add the confectioners sugar and vanilla.

title: french dressing(homemade)
directions: Blend vinegar, oil and sugar.
Add catsup and onion.
Pour into bottles.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon fluff frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar and lemon until fluffy.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Will cover tops of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fried venison
directions: Cut venison into strips about 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Chill 1/2 hour. Heat oil in a skillet and fry the meat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pita chips
directions: Cut pita bread into quarters.
Separate bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush melted butter on tops of bread.
Sprinkle a little garlic salt on bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: At room temperature, cream together butter and brown sugar. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle 1 cup nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whip cream cake
directions: Sit butter out the day before (2 days won't hurt).
Cream the butter and sugar together.
Blend in the eggs, one at a time. Blend in the whipping cream and sifted flour.
Add the lemon extract and continue to blend until smooth.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan generously.
Place in a cold oven and bake at 315° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Do not preheat oven.)

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add marshmallows, fruit cocktail and pineapple. Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze until firm, approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: fantastic lemon cake
directions: Generously butter a 9 inch-12 cup Turk's head mold or Bundt or tube pan. Dust lightly with flour.

title: crabmeat cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika in medium size bowl and beat until mixed well. Spread in small 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot from oven with crackers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion
and
celery
in
pan with butter. Add both soups, rice and broccoli.	Let simmer. Place in casserole dish and bake for
to 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and place Cheez Whiz
on top, then put back in oven for about 5 to 10 minutes or until melted good.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour and nuts together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: creole okra(microwave)
directions: Place bacon in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar with oleo.
Add eggs and mix flour and soda.
Add nuts and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Add sugar and lemon juice to hot water. Cook until sugar dissolves. Add figs and cook rapidly 10 minutes. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Add sliced lemons and continue cooking rapidly until figs are clear, about 10 to 15 minutes. (If syrup becomes too thick before figs become clear, add boiling water, 1/4 cup at a time.)

Cover and let stand 12 to 24 hours in a cool place. Pack into hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Process half pints and pints 30 minutes at 180° to 185° in hot water bath. Yield: About 10 half pints.

title: orange salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine lettuce, oranges and peanuts; toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: layered salad
directions: Divide in half and place in 13 x 9-inch pan in order given. Pack down.
Make a day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat together cottage cheese, melted butter and eggs, adding one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sugar, milk, flour, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Add 1 cup chopped dates or raisins.
Mix well.
Place in crust.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour or until set.
Before baking, sprinkle top with chopped nuts or coconut.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except a few of the oranges and the cherries.
Put in pretty glass dish and decorate top with mandarin oranges and cherries.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add spices, salt, vanilla, melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually add hot milk.
Mix together rice, raisins and remaining 1/2 cup sugar and turn into baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over rice.
Set baking dish in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 325° until knife, when inserted, emerges clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrate for 30 seconds.
Blend in ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth.
Freeze until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
Add bread crumbs (saving 2 tablespoons for top), cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Top with the 2 tablespoons of crumbs; dot with the other 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: atlanta delight
directions: Simmer the ingredients for a few hours.
Strain.
Serve hot or cold.

title: orange rolls
directions: Combine flour, shortening, sugar, orange rind, and salt in a bowl. Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg and stir. Add mixture to flour and stir well.
Add milk.
Stir to combine.
On floured surface, knead dough, shape into a large ball and place in a greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place free from drafts for about 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Punch down and divide into 36 equal pieces.
Form into balls.
Grease muffin pan.
Place 3 balls into each muffin.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake rolls 15 - 20 minutes or until done.
Remove immediately from pan and place on wire rack to cool slightly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix well and press in the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: kolotches cookies
directions: Put 6 cups flour in bowl, add sugar and salt.
Mix yeast in 1/4 c. warm water.
Beat eggs till well mixed; add sour cream to eggs; add yeast and mix.
Take flour, sugar and salt and butter; mix as for pie dough.
Add egg, sour cream and yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour as needed.
Knead for 20 minutes.
Let rise in warm place till double in size.
Press small amounts on floured surface.
Fill with filling.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat with onion and pepper.
Drain. Add beans, barbecue sauce and sugar.
Simmer 20 or 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste, pepperoni, mushrooms (optional), salt and oregano.
Add this to uncooked dumpling noodles and water in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Add Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: pasta salad(servings:  10)
directions: Combine cooked and drained macaroni with drained green beans, diced carrots, drained red kidney beans, drained peas, chopped onion, chopped celery and chopped green pepper.
Mix together Miracle Whip, prepared mustard, milk or half and half and sugar. Toss gently with salad.
Refrigerate.
Keeps long time.
Makes a large amount.
Tastes even better second day.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared casserole. Bake until set, 50 to 60 minutes or microwave on Medium 12 minutes, then on High 3 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Each 1/2 cup serving provides 1 fat, 1/2 protein, 1/2 bread and 20 calories.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Mix all ingredients well; cover and simmer, covered, for 4 hours.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cool corn bread into large bowl.
Add onion, pepper, tomato and eggs.
Add bacon and mix together with the Miracle Whip.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve cool.

title: no cook oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine and heat to boiling for 3 1/2 minutes.
Spoon out onto wax paper and cool.

title: crown royal balls
directions: Mix pecans, powdered sugar, butter, Crown Royal and dash of salt together.
Roll into balls.
Let set in cool place until chilled.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. Dip in paraffin using a hot pin or similar utensil liken to a toothpick.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and oil.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll dough into balls.
Dip bottom of glass tumbler in sugar and press out balls.
Bake at 325° on greased cookie sheet until lightly browned.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and ginger; set aside. In a large bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin, egg product and oil.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture; stir just until moistened.
Fold in berries and nuts.

title: baked breaded pork chops(amish recipe)
directions: Add salt and pepper to crumbs.
Beat egg and add milk.
Dip chops in liquid and roll in crumbs; put 3 tablespoons oil in a skillet and brown chops.
Place chops in baking dish and add boiling water.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy chocolate balls
directions: Melt chocolate bars in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High; stir once.
Stir until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold 8 ounces Cool Whip (thawed) into chocolate.
Mixture will thicken. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 2/3 cup finely crushed vanilla wafers (blender gives good consistency).
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 66.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Boil together the next 5 ingredients and pour over the cabbage mixture.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Once a day, open and stir. Will keep in container for more than a week.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, then add pumpkin.
Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: dressing for fruit
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in sour cream.
Will keep about 2 weeks.
Use on any fruit (fresh, frozen or canned).

title: frozen cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel and slice 2 quarts cucumbers.
Slice the onion and put in bowl.
Cover with the salt; toss.
Cover and let stand 2 hours. Drain off liquid; do not wash.
Cover with sugar.
Add vinegar; toss again.
Bag and freeze.
Will keep several months.

title: red cinnamon hardtack candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Boil to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased cake pan; spread evenly.
When cool, break into pieces by pounding with a large spoon.
Coat with powdered sugar.

title: lemon pepper burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ground beef, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, 1 tsp. lemon pepper and garlic powder, mixing lightly but thoroughly. Shape into four 1/2 inch thick patties. Press remaining lemon pepper evenly onto both sides of patties. Pan fry, grill or broil patties 10 to 13 minutes or until no longer pink in center.

title: pork tenderloin with mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate pork for several hours, turning occasionally.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding mix and whole can of crushed pineapple together.
Add rinsed off marshmallows and Cool Whip. Stir until all the ingredients are well mixed.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: yummy cracker jacks
directions: Cook margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes at a medium boil.
Take off heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Add gelatin and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth (use hand beater if necessary to remove lumps).
Cool.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp.
Put into greased mold and chill.

title: meal in a pot
directions: Arrange cabbage in pot.
Place potatoes on top.
Add water and seasonings; cook until tender.
Cut sausage in pieces and cook 10 minutes longer.
Arrange on platter and serve.

title: viola's oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats and water together for 20 minutes.
Cover and set aside.
Cream sugars and shortening.
