Add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 x 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: potato surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Cool jello and add raspberries and sherbet.
Add pineapple.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from pepper.
Grind peppers in food chopper or processor.
In a large pot, combine peppers, sugar and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add Certo and boil 1 minute longer.
Pour into jars. Makes about 4 1/2 pints.
Shake jars frequently by turning them upside down until jelly sets.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Cook strawberries and tapioca until thick; cool. In separate bowl, whip cream cheese until soft; add condensed cream and beat. Add egg yolks, one at a time then add lemon juice. Pour the cream cheese mixture into the graham cracker crust; pour strawberry topping on pie.

title: ham and corn quiche
directions: Unroll crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an 8-inch pie pan; press to form a crust.
Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Sprinkle parsley flakes over filling.
Cover edges of crust with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Bake longer if filling isn't set and crust isn't golden brown.
Cool for about 5 minutes before serving.

title: sunny scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat potatoes with combined flour and seasoning.
Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Heat Velveeta cheese and milk over low heat; add green peppers, onions and pimento.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: 1 loaf of bread or 1 dozen rolls
directions: Heat shortening and milk until warm; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball and place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Place in a greased bread pan until double again.
Let rise and bake about 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add egg yolks and 1/2 cup of the milk, mix well, then add rest of milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: black-eyed pea salad 2
directions: Combine ingredients and toss.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together into a large mixing bowl, the flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix well until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed.
Bake in a lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: english lemon tea cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk to butter mixture. Pour batter in greased 9 x 5 x 3 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jello pie
directions: Cook eggs, pineapple juice and sugar until thick.
Stir in jello and cool.
Beat frozen Pet milk until light and fluffy.
Add jello mixture.
Line pie pan with vanilla wafers and pour in mixture.
Freeze until thick.

title: stuffed peppers(microwave)
directions: Cook split peppers for 5 minutes in microwave.
Mix remaining ingredients in medium bowl, except for barbecue sauce.
Spoon meat mixture into green pepper halves.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave 25 minutes on roast (140°) or until meat is done.
Top with barbecue sauce and cook for 1 minute.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and chocolate together.
Cream shortening and sugar until very smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend well and add food coloring and vanilla.
Mix buttermilk, vinegar and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix alternating to the creamed mixture.
Blend at slow speed between each addition.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This can be put in three cake pans.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onions and carrots until soft. Drain water. Mix sour cream, flour and paprika. Add a little milk to mix well, then add to pot of potatoes. Add milk, pepper, salt, bacon and cheese and simmer until it is as thick as you like it.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour melted butter over sugar.
Beat eggs well.
Pour over butter and sugar.
Add buttermilk, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour into crust; bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cream-cheese lime pie
directions: About 3 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day:
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup milk.
Reduce speed to low; add pudding mix, undiluted limeade concentrate and remaining 1 cup milk.
Beat just until blended. Fold in 2 cups whipped topping; spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate pie until cream cheese filling is firm enough to slice, at least 3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine vegetables, salt and 6 cups water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes.
Simmer until veggies are tender.
Add oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Season with pepper.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, mix meal, sour cream, corn and well beaten eggs together.
Bake in greased 10-inch skillet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except cookie crumbs in a mixing bowl. Place in lightly oiled baking dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or chilled with crumbled wafers sprinkled on top.
A heart healthy dessert.

title: key lime pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat until smooth. Add other ingredients.
Place in crust of your choice and chill.

title: rumaki(good appetizer.  need to triple recipe.)
directions: Cut chicken livers into halves; cut each water chestnut into 3 pieces.
Pour teriyaki sauce on livers and water chestnuts in bowl.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours; drain.* Cut bacon slices into halves.
Wrap a piece of liver and a piece of water chestnut in each bacon piece.
Secure with wooden pick; roll in brown sugar. Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat, turning occasionally, until bacon is crisp, about 10 minutes.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: bennie's corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in dish and mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs well. Add eggs, corn and milk to mixture.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: souffleed omelet
directions: Separate the egg yolks from the egg whites.
Beat the yolks with the granulated sugar and rum until well blended.
Beat the until they are firm but not stiff.
Gently fold the whites into yolk mixture.
Melt the butter in a 10 or 12-inch ovenproof skillet.
When butter sizzles, turn the eggs into the skillet and cook over a low flame for about 7 minutes.
Sprinkle the omelet with confectioners sugar and pass it under the broiler for about 2 minutes until glazed.
Serve immediately.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese with the taco seasoning mix. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch flat bowl.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese, sliced black olives and chopped onion.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
In medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook until tender.
Cut thin slice from top of potatoes.
Scoop out potatoes; mash with butter, salt, thyme and oregano.
Stir in bacon, mushrooms and onion.
Pack mixture back into potato shells. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken on a cloud
directions: Sift one cup flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine 3 well beaten eggs,
1 1/2 cups milk, 1/4 cup margarine or butter (melted) and 1/4 cup chopped parsley.
Mix with dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for one hour or until tender.

title: marinated sunday salad
directions: Fill container about 1/2 way with vinegar (I prefer red wine vinegar).
Fill
to
3/4 with water and sprinkle sugar on top. Stir
in and let stand approximately 30 minutes.
Always served on Sunday at Corapeake Country Buffet.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in a large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and water over medium heat.
Add nuts and continue cooking, stirring frequently, until there is no syrup left.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet and separate with fork. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: cucumber-dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with sliced raw carrots, celery, etc.

title: pork ribs adobo
directions: Place pork ribs in a large pot and add all the ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium low. Simmer for about an hour or until all the liquid has been absorbed by the meat and the meat is soft and tender. Remove meat and place in a serving platter and garnish with the green onion leaves.

title: peach bavarian
directions: In saucepan, combine gelatin, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add crushed peaches.
Chill until mixture mounds from spoon.
Fold peach mixture into whipped cream.
May add few drops food coloring (red and yellow) to tint peach color.
Pour into 4-cup mold and chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: patriotic pastries(children's cooking)
directions: Cut bread with star-shaped cookie cutter; spread with butter. Sprinkle with red Jell-O.
Toast.
Preparation:
5 minutes.

title: chicken scarpariello
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; dredge in flour.
Add to butter and oil; saute in pan.
Let it brown (golden).
Remove chicken from pan.
Place in oven-tempered dish.
Put in garlic, shallots and sun-dried tomatoes; saute 30 seconds.
Add sherry; reduce by half, then add beef stock.
Heat until thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water thoroughly, then cool. Fold into the Jell-O all at once the strawberries, pineapple with juice, bananas and nuts.
Put half of the mixture into mold. Spread with 1/2 pint sour cream.
Repeat with the rest of the strawberry mixture. Refrigerate until firm. Spread evenly with another 1/2 pint sour cream.

title: amber's cookies
directions: Melt white bark and dip in Ritz Bits.
Place on wax paper to cool. Grab a handful and a glass of milk.
Yum! Yum!

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash lettuce thoroughly and drain; break into small pieces. Layer lettuce in bottom of a large mixing bowl.
Follow each ingredient as shown step by step with the chopped onion second, the drained Veg-All third and the drained chestnuts fourth. Spoon on mayonnaise fifth.
Spread on grated cheese sixth topped with bacon bits.
Chill and serve with any meal.

title: robby's fruit stuff salad
directions: Mix well and let set overnight in the fridge.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix boiling water and jello, stirring until dissolved.
Add cold water and juices.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Marinate meat of choice for 4 to 5 hours.

title: polish mistake
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage.
Pour off fat.
Add cheese to meat.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Spread on rye bread.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter baking sheets. Combine butter and sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; mix dry ingredients together and add to butter. CHILL. Roll out and cut with your favorite cookie cutters. Decorate with sprinkles. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are light brown on edges. Cool on wire rack.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt
oleo or butter in baking dish.
In separate bowl, put fruit and add sugar
to
taste.
Cherries call for 3/4 cup sugar. Let stand until batter is ready.

title: surprise salad
directions: Chop apples and candy.
Quickly mix pudding and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Add apples and candy.
Refrigerate.

title: pralines
directions: In heavy pan, mix first 4 ingredients.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until ingredients reach 230° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until color begins to change, then working very quickly, drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Line the bottom of baked pie crust with the strawberries (fresh ones); mash the frozen strawberries.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add sugar and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to hot mixture food coloring. Pour over the strawberries.
Be sure the glaze is cool before pouring on berries in crust.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with sweetened whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Fill unbaked crust with rhubarb.
Mix flour, sugar and butter. Add beaten egg yolks to mixture.
Spread over rhubarb then bake at 350° until rhubarb is soft.
Beat egg whites, add 4 tablespoons sugar; spread on top of pie.
Put back in oven until brown.

title: sgt. moore's corn dip
directions: Mix together and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Use corn chip scoops.

title: salmon salad
directions: Break fettuccine into 6-inch pieces.
Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water, drain again.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon pudding and liquid from pineapple and fruit cocktail with whisk until dissolved.
Add the remaining ingredients, starting with nutmeg.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: ice cream pudding dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with margarine.
Reserve 1 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Blend pudding and milk together.
Add ice cream and mix until smooth.
Pour over crumbs.
Spread whipped topping over ice cream mixture.
Sprinkle the 1 cup crumbs and chopped peanuts on top.
Cover and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer for several minutes before serving.
Can also use chocolate pudding and ice cream or make 1 layer chocolate and 1 layer vanilla.

title: quick and easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven.
Add macaroni, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sue's raspberry (or strawberry) salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream, in order listed. Pour half the gelatin mixture into a mold which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Leave remaining half at room temperature. Refrigerate the mold until set but still sticky.
Spread the sour cream on top, then pour the remaining gelatin mixture on top. Cover and refrigerate.

title: hot bacon dip
directions: Mix with mixer until cream cheese is smooth.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with extra crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with raw veggies, crackers, bread cubes, etc.

title: hot buttered tomato juice
directions: Heat, but do not boil. Serve in mugs with lemon or lime wedge garnishes.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in casserole; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine other ingredients and pour over fruit; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Cover cookie sheet with parchment paper or foil; draw plate-sized circle in center.
Beat egg whites, salt and vinegar until soft peaks form.
Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Gradually add to egg whites until very stiff peaks form.	Spread in circle and mound around edge, making shell form (build up 1 3/4-inches on sides).
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and let dry in oven about 2 hours.
Peel off.
Can make the day before and freeze.

title: cherry-pecan loaf
directions: In large bowl, cream butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In a smaller bowl, stir flour, soda and salt.
Add this to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Beat all.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool. Make glaze mixture of powdered sugar and milk to mix.
Put over cooled loaf as glaze.

title: fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in a large pan.
Boil until fudge will form a soft ball when dropped into a cup of cold water.
Remove from stove; cool and continue to stir.
(Can put bottom of pan into sink of cold water.)
As soon as it starts to harden, pour on a margarine covered platter.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add onion, buttermilk and egg. Drop by rounded spoonfuls into fresh hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: christmas tree relish tray
directions: You will also need 1 Styrofoam cone, about 10 or 12 inches high and toothpicks.

title: stromboli
directions: Place dough on lightly greased baking sheet; pat to a 15 x 10-inch rectangle. Arrange ham slices lengthwise down center; place salami on top. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon basil and 1/4 teaspoon oregano. Arrange Provolone cheese over herbs; top with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with remaining herbs. Moisten all edges of dough with water.
Bring each long edge of dough to center; press edges together. Brush dough with 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle with corn meal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut up the oranges and apples in small pieces.

Drain the juice from the pineapple and do not use the juice in the salad. Add to fruit. Stir in the box of instant vanilla pudding mix from the box making sure all the fruit is covered well. Raisins, coconut and cherries may be added. Will keep for days in refrigerator in a covered bowl.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet. Pour off drippings. Sprinkle taco seasoning mix over meat. Stir in tomato sauce and kidney beans. Cook slowly 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni as directed on package; drain well.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: arroz con leche(rice pudding - cuban cookery)
directions: Boil water with the cinnamon sticks and lemon peels; add rice and cook it covered until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add to the milk which has been heated in another large pot in which the sugar was added at the end to dissolve better.
Cook at medium heat on the stove burner approximately 1 hour, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking to bottom of pot.
Do not let it get too thick.

title: old south wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain on paper towel (or microwave and save fat).
Add vinegar to fat and bring to boil.
Tear lettuce to bite size (make ahead of time while bacon cooks).
Add onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine sugar and flour in paper or plastic bag.
Shake meat in bag to coat.
Brown in hot shortening.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in prepared bite-sized vegetables, except peas. Cook 30 minutes, covered.
Add peas and continue cooking about 15 minutes.
Water may be added if needed during the 2 hour cooking. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Pour into greased, shallow baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops with cream sauce
directions: Fry bacon in skillet, save drippings.
Mix egg and milk together.
Dip pork chops in flour, then egg mixture, then bread crumbs.
Brown pork chops in bacon drippings.
Pour half of the 1/2 pint of whipping cream over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Remove pork chops and add remaining half and half to pan.
Heat to a boil; add bacon (crumbled) into sauce.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds at 350° until light brown.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, oil and flavor packet for dressing; set aside. Combine cabbage, onions, noodles and almonds; set aside.
Do not add dressing until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and make 2 layers with crumbled crust in between and on bottom and top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Wash and steam until tender; drain.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in flour and add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add onion, salt, pepper and cream cheese.
Stir until cream cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Combine sauce with broccoli in a casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in greased baking dish (8 x 12-inch unless more fruit is used).
Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Pour hot sauce over rhubarb. Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and margarine; sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Put all vegies in a large salad bowl.
Set aside.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Brown beef.
Combine nacho cheese soup and cream of chicken soup in a saucepan.
Heat.
Heat a small amount of oil in a fry pan.
Dip tortillas in oil to soften.
Drain on paper towel. Spoon beef on each tortilla; add a teaspoon of onion and sprinkle with sharp cheese.
Roll up and place in a casserole dish, seam side down.
Repeat for each tortilla.
Add green chilies to soups and pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: twinkies toffee temptation
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package.
Set aside. Slice Twinkies in half, lengthwise.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with bottom halves of Twinkies, cream filling sides up.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crushed candy.
Pour on pudding.
Arrange top halves of Twinkies over pudding.
Spread on Cool Whip. Top with remaining candy. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: granny frye's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a stiff ball. Refrigerate overnight. Roll out next day. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked sole with lemon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish. Dot 3 tablespoons butter on top of fish.
Heat chicken broth and lemon juice through.
Don't boil.
Grease large shallow baking pan.
Place fish in pan.
Stir yolks and water together.
Stir flour and melted butter together.
Mix with chicken broth and lemon juice.
Pour over fish.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pineapple together.
Add dry pudding powder and mix.
Chill.

title: old fashion sugar cookies(my grandma stidd's recipe)
directions: Cream together the sugar and lard.
Mix together the beaten eggs, baking powder, soda, nutmeg, salt and sour cream.
Add the flour.
Combine the creamed mixture to the flour mixture.
Dough is very soft.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake at 350° until bottom is light brown.
Cookies are soft.
Sprinkle with colored sugar before baking.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 2 cups hot water. Add Jell-O and applesauce.
Put half of the mixture in mold.
Let set. Mix softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup mayonnaise. Add nuts.
Put on top of hardened Jell-O.
Pour rest of Jell-O on top and let set until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Stir until cranberry sauce melts.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture into mold and chill until firm.
Let remaining 1/2 stand at room temperature.
When first 1/2 is firm, spread sour cream evenly over top.
Spoon remainder of jello over sour cream.
Chill overnight.

title: bird's nests
directions: Use a 4-inch diameter strainer or flour sifter.
Dip in hot oil to coat.
Shake off excess.
Line strainer with shredded potatoes. Place a 2-inch strainer on top of potatoes to keep in place.
Dip into hot oil until golden brown.
Tap out of strainer onto paper towels.
Loosen with knife if necessary.
Continue until all potatoes are cooked.
Fill with creamed chicken or any stir-fry recipe.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat thoroughly. Place in oven at 275° and bake for 1 hour.
Turn heat to 300° and bake for another hour or until done.

title: salata (tossed salad)
directions: Cut tomatoes in cubes.
Cut the lettuce; peel and cut cucumber.
Mix tomatoes, lettuce and cucumber.
Mash garlic with a sprinkle of salt and add to mixture.
Add one bunch of chopped green onions.
Wash and add some fresh green mint if it is in season.
(If not, sprinkle on dried mint.)
Squeeze lemon and add to mix.
Spread with oil and some pepper.
Mix the ingredients and enjoy a breath-taking of garlic and onions.
Serves 4 people.

title: *sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually and cream together.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Measure and sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until flour disappears. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: skillet pot roast
directions: In deep 12-inch skillet, brown meat on all sides in hot fat. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion salt. Add 1/2 cup water. Cover tightly and simmer about 2 1/2 hours, adding more water if necessary. Add potatoes and carrots. Cook for 30 minutes. Add green beans, squash and small onions. For each serving, allow 1 small squash and 2 onions. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Some meat will be leftover for another meal.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; cut a slice of stem end and remove seeds and membrane.
Parboil peppers 5 minutes in a small amount of boiling, salted water; drain and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-a-Roni according to package directions. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Layer over rice, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cut up cooked chicken.
Mix soups and milk; pour over chicken and rice mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mama bic's kahlua
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and water.
Add coffee.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Take off fire and add vanilla. Cool and add vodka.

title: pork 'n beans
directions: Saute onions in margarine.

In baking dish combine pork and beans, brown sugar, onions, mustard and ketchup. Stir. Cook 2 to 3 slices bacon; chop up and add to dish. Stir. Slice remaining raw bacon into quarters. Add to top of baking dish. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; add salt.
Drain cabbage and add the cheese, milk, butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown in casserole dish.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Marinate meat for 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Cook on grill 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Mix coconut, pecans and butter in skillet, cook until light brown.
Set aside.

title: daddy's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix remaining ingredients with ground beef. If too thick, you may add water. Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until all contents are done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Combine 6 tablespoons butter, flour, salt, curry powder and milk into a sauce.
Cook mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter for about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and shrimp to sauce in baking dish. Cover mixture well with crumbs and bake slowly until crumbs are nicely browned, about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: crab canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffins.
Spread onto the split English muffins. Toast in the oven until hot and bubbly.
Cut each muffin into 4 wedges.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Add 3 cups of flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 cup pecans, 1 1/2 cup fresh apples or applesauce and 1 1/4 cup of cooking oil; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch baking pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix together oil and eggs.
Add sugar, then carrot baby food and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture, then nuts (if desired).
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well. Mix all other ingredients together. Add cherries last and lightly toss. Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 to 6 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mint dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Put 2 cups of crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Soften mint ice cream and put over crumb crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: pollo guisado
directions: Put 3 cups of rice in a pot with 5 1/2 cups of water, along with 1/2 of the scallions, oil, 1 dash of salt and 2 diced garlic cloves. Put rice to boil on medium; stir occasionally.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding in milk.
Add all fruits.

title: diabetic cool-la-la lime pie filling
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Slowly add artificial sweetener and continue beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add green coloring, cream, lime juice and grated peel.
Mix well.
Pour into freezing tray and freeze until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Soak broccoli in ice cold salt water for 2 to 3 minutes before breaking apart.
Mix all together and toss with Hellmann's mayonnaise.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts on bottom of a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. (An 11 x 15 pan is even better.) Spread coconut over nuts. Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over coconut. Soften margarine and cream cheese. Add confectioners sugar and mix well. Pour over cake mix evenly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pecan cheese tarts
directions: Cream butter and cheese smooth.
Add flour and mix well (should resemble pie crust).
Add 1/2 teaspoon water if necessary to make dough cling together.
Divide into 24 round balls, flatten and line tart tins or muffin pans.

title: chicken with cheese topping
directions: Soak chicken breasts in egg with garlic powder (1 hour). Bread the chicken pieces and brown in oleo.
Place in glass baking dish. Add the wine.
Cover with Muenster cheese, sliced. Bake, covered, 15 minutes at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and broccoli potato topper
directions: Scrub medium baking potatoes.
Brush with salad oil.
Wrap each in piece of foil, overlapping ends.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes on grill or right on top of coals.
Turn occasionally.
Pinch to tell when done.
Cut crisscross with fork in top of package and push on ends to fluff.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Beat margarine on medium speed with electric mixer until softened.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Slowly beat in flour until well combined.
Spread or pat dough on bottom of 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until lightly browned on edges.
